  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elkanah and His Wives'
      title: Elkanah and His Wives
      number: 1
      content: '  There was a certain man of Ramathaim-zophim, of the hill country
        of Ephraim, named Elkanah the son of Jeroham, the son of Elihu, the son of
        Tohu, the son of Zuph, an Ephraimite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He had two wives, one named Hannah and the other named Peninnah.
        Peninnah had children, but Hannah had none.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'This man went up from his city each year to worship and sacrifice
        to the Lord of hosts at Shiloh. Hophni and Phinehas, the two sons of Eli,
        were priests to the Lord there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the day came that Elkanah sacrificed, he would give portions
        [of the sacrificial meat] to Peninnah his wife and all her sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But to Hannah he would give a double portion, because he loved Hannah,
        but the Lord had given her no children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Hannah\u2019s rival provoked her bitterly, to irritate and embarrass
        her, because the Lord had left her childless. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So it happened year after year, whenever she went up to the house
        of the Lord, Peninnah provoked her; so she wept and would not eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Elkanah her husband said to her, \u201CHannah, why do you cry
        and why do you not eat? Why are you so sad and discontent? Am I not better
        to you than ten sons?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Hannah got up after eating and drinking in Shiloh. Now Eli the
        priest was sitting on his seat beside the doorpost of the temple (tabernacle)
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Hannah was greatly distressed, and she prayed to the Lord and wept
        in anguish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "She made a vow, saying, \u201CO Lord of hosts, if You will indeed
        look on the affliction (suffering) of Your maidservant and remember, and
        not forget Your maidservant, but will give Your maidservant a son, then I
        will give him to the Lord all the days of his life; a razor shall never touch
        his head.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now it happened as she continued praying before the Lord, that Eli
        was watching her mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hannah was speaking in her heart (mind); only her lips were moving,
        and her voice was not heard, so Eli thought she was drunk. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Eli said to her, \u201CHow long will you make yourself drunk? Get
        rid of your wine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But Hannah answered, \u201CNo, my lord, I am a woman with a despairing
        spirit. I have not been drinking wine or any intoxicating drink, but I have
        poured out my soul before the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Do not regard your maidservant as a wicked and worthless woman, for
        I have spoken until now out of my great concern and [bitter] provocation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Eli answered and said, \u201CGo in peace; and may the God of
        Israel grant your petition that you have asked of Him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Samuel Is Born to Hannah'
      title: Samuel Is Born to Hannah
      number: 18
      content: "Hannah said, \u201CLet your maidservant find grace and favor in your
        sight.\u201D So the woman went on her way and ate, and her face was no longer
        sad.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The family got up early the next morning, worshiped before the Lord,
        and returned to their home in Ramah. Elkanah knew Hannah his wife, and the
        Lord remembered her [prayer]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "It came about in due time, after Hannah had conceived, that she gave
        birth to a son; she named him Samuel, saying, \u201CBecause I have asked
        for him from the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the man Elkanah and all his household went up to offer to the
        Lord the yearly sacrifice and pay his vow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Hannah did not go up, for she said to her husband, \u201CI will
        not go up until the child is weaned; and then I will bring him, so that he
        may appear before the Lord and remain there as long as he lives.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Elkanah her husband said to her, \u201CDo what seems best to you.
        Wait until you have weaned him; only may the Lord establish and confirm His
        word.\u201D So the woman remained [behind] and nursed her son until she weaned
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Now when she had weaned him, she took him up with her, along with
        a three-year-old bull, an ephah of flour, and a leather bottle of wine [to
        pour over the burnt offering for a sweet fragrance], and she brought Samuel
        to the Lord\u2019s house in Shiloh, although the child was young. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then they slaughtered the bull, and brought the child to Eli. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Hannah said, \u201COh, my lord! As [surely as] your soul lives, my
        lord, I am the woman who stood beside you here, praying to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For this child I prayed, and the Lord has granted me my request which
        I asked of Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Therefore I have also dedicated him to the Lord; as long as he lives
        he is dedicated to the Lord.\u201D And they worshiped the Lord there."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hannah\u2019s Song of Thanksgiving"
      title: "Hannah\u2019s Song of Thanksgiving"
      number: 1
      content: "  Hannah prayed and said,\u201CMy heart rejoices and triumphs in
        the Lord;My horn (strength) is lifted up in the Lord,My mouth has opened
        wide [to speak boldly] against my enemies,Because I rejoice in Your salvation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There is no one holy like the Lord,There is no one besides You,There
        is no Rock like our God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do not go on boasting so very proudly,Do not let arrogance come out
        of your mouth;For the Lord is a God of knowledge,And by Him actions are weighed
        (examined).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The bows of the mighty are broken,But those who have stumbled equip
        themselves with strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Those who were full hire themselves out for bread,But those who were
        hungry cease [to hunger].Even the barren [woman] gives birth to seven,But
        she who has many children withers away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The Lord puts to death and makes alive;He brings down to Sheol (the
        grave) and raises up [from the grave].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Lord makes poor and makes rich;He brings low and He lifts up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "He raises up the poor from the dust,He lifts up the needy from the
        ash heapTo make them sit with nobles,And inherit a seat of honor and glory;For
        the pillars of the earth are the Lord\u2019s,And He set the land on them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He guards the feet of His godly (faithful) ones,But the wicked ones
        are silenced and perish in darkness;For a man shall not prevail by might.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The adversaries of the Lord will be broken to pieces;He will thunder
        against them in the heavens,The Lord will judge the ends of the earth;And
        He will give strength to His king,And will exalt the horn (strength) of His
        anointed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: "11: The Sin of Eli\u2019s Sons"
      title: "The Sin of Eli\u2019s Sons"
      number: 11
      content: 'Elkanah [and his wife Hannah] returned to Ramah to his house. But
        the child [Samuel] served the Lord  under the guidance of Eli the priest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Eli [Hophni and Phinehas] were worthless (dishonorable,
        unprincipled) men; they did not know [nor respect] the Lord  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and the custom of the priests with [the sacrifices of] the people.
        When any man was offering a sacrifice, the priest\u2019s servant would come
        while the meat was boiling, with a three-pronged [meat] fork in his hand; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then he would thrust it into the pan, or kettle, or caldron, or pot;
        everything that the fork brought up the priest would take for himself. This
        is what they did in Shiloh to all [the sacrifices of] the Israelites who
        came there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Also, before they burned (offered) the fat, the priest\u2019s servant
        would come and say to the man who was sacrificing, \u201CGive the priest
        meat to roast, since he will not accept boiled meat from you, only raw.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "If the man said to him, \u201CCertainly they are to burn (offer)
        the fat first, and then you may take as much as you want,\u201D then the
        priest\u2019s servant would say, \u201CNo! You shall give it to me now or
        I will take it by force.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Samuel before the Lord as a Boy'
      title: Samuel before the Lord as a Boy
      number: 17
      content: 'So the sin of the [two] young men [Hophni and Phinehas] was very
        great before the Lord, for the men treated the offering of the Lord disrespectfully.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now Samuel was ministering before the Lord, as a child dressed in
        a linen ephod [a sacred item of priestly clothing]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Moreover, his mother would make him a little robe and would bring
        it up to him each year when she came up with her husband to offer the yearly
        sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Eli would bless Elkanah and his wife and say, \u201CMay the
        Lord give you children by this woman in place of the one she asked for which
        was dedicated to the Lord.\u201D Then they would return to their own home.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Eli Rebukes His Sons'
      title: Eli Rebukes His Sons
      number: 21
      content: 'And [the time came when] the Lord visited Hannah, so that she conceived
        and gave birth to three sons and two daughters. And the boy Samuel grew before
        the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now Eli was very old; and he heard about everything that his sons
        were doing to all [the people of] Israel, and how they were lying with the
        women who served at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting (tabernacle). '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Eli said to them, \u201CWhy do you do such things, the evil things
        that I hear from all these people? "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "No, my sons; for the report that I keep hearing from the passers-by
        among the Lord\u2019s people is not good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "If one man does wrong and sins against another, God will intercede
        (arbitrate) for him; but if a man does wrong to the Lord, who can intercede
        for him?\u201D But they would not listen to their father, for it was the
        Lord\u2019s will to put them to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But the boy Samuel continued to grow in stature and in favor both
        with the Lord and with men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then a man of God (prophet) came to Eli and said to him, \u201CThus
        says the Lord: \u2018Did I not plainly reveal Myself to the house of your
        father (ancestor) when they were in Egypt in bondage to Pharaoh\u2019s house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Moreover, I selected him out of all the tribes of Israel to be My
        priest, to go up to My altar, to burn incense, to wear an ephod before Me.
        And [from then on] I gave to the house of your father all the fire offerings
        of the sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Why then do you kick at (despise) My sacrifice and My offering which
        I commanded in My dwelling place, and honor your sons more than Me, by fattening
        yourselves with the choicest part of every offering of My people Israel?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Therefore the Lord God of Israel declares, \u2018I did indeed say
        that your house and that of [Aaron] your father would walk [in priestly service]
        before Me forever.\u2019 But now the Lord declares, \u2018Far be it from
        Me\u2014for those who honor Me I will honor, and those who despise Me will
        be insignificant and contemptible. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Behold, the time is coming when I will cut off your strength and
        the strength of your father\u2019s house, so that there will not be an old
        man in your house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'You will look at the distress of My  house (the tabernacle), in spite
        of all the good which God will do for Israel, and there will never again
        be an old man in your house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Yet I will not cut off every man of yours from My altar; your eyes
        will fail from weeping and your soul will grieve, and all those born in your
        house will die as men [in the prime of life]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'This will be the sign to you which shall come concerning your two
        sons, Hophni and Phinehas: on the same day both of them shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'But I will raise up for Myself a faithful priest who will do according
        to what is in My heart and in My soul; and I will build him a permanent and
        enduring house, and he will walk before My anointed forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And it will happen that everyone who is left in your house will come
        and bow down to him for a piece of silver and a loaf of bread and say, \u201CPlease
        assign me to one of the priest\u2019s offices so I may eat a piece of bread.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Prophetic Call to Samuel'
      title: The Prophetic Call to Samuel
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the boy Samuel was attending to the service of the Lord  under
        the supervision of Eli. The word of the Lord was rare and precious in those
        days; visions [that is, new revelations of divine truth] were not widespread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yet it happened at that time, as Eli was lying down in his own place
        (now his eyesight had begun to grow dim and he could not see well). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the [oil] lamp of God had not yet gone out, and Samuel was lying
        down in the temple of the Lord, where the ark of God was, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "that the Lord called Samuel, and he answered, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He ran to Eli and said, \u201CHere I am, for you called me.\u201D
        But Eli said, \u201CI did not call you; lie down again.\u201D So he went
        and lay down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the Lord called yet again, \u201CSamuel!\u201D So Samuel got
        up and went to Eli and said, \u201CHere I am, for you called me.\u201D But
        Eli answered, \u201CI did not call, my son; lie down again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now Samuel did not yet know [or personally experience] the Lord,
        and the word of the Lord was not yet revealed [directly] to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So the Lord called Samuel a third time. And he stood and went to
        Eli and said, \u201CHere I am, for you did call me.\u201D Then Eli understood
        that it was the Lord [who was] calling the boy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Eli said to Samuel, \u201CGo, lie down, and it shall be that if
        He calls you, you shall say, \u2018Speak, Lord, for Your servant is listening.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        So Samuel went and lay down in his place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the Lord came and stood and called as at the previous times,
        \u201CSamuel! Samuel!\u201D Then Samuel answered, \u201CSpeak, for Your servant
        is listening.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The Lord said to Samuel, \u201CBehold, I am about to do a thing in
        Israel at which both ears of everyone who hears it will ring. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On that day I will carry out against Eli everything that I have spoken
        concerning his house (family), from beginning to end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now I have told him that I am about to judge his house forever for
        the sinful behavior which he knew [was happening], because his sons were
        bringing a curse on themselves [dishonoring and blaspheming God] and he did
        not rebuke them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore I have sworn to the house of Eli that the sinful behavior
        of Eli\u2019s house (family) shall not be atoned for by sacrifice or offering
        forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So Samuel lay down until morning. Then he opened the doors of the
        Lord\u2019s house. But Samuel was afraid to tell the vision to Eli. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Eli called Samuel and said, \u201CSamuel, my son.\u201D And he
        answered, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Eli said, \u201CWhat is it that He said to you? Please do not
        hide it from me. May God do the same to you, and more also, if you hide from
        me anything of all that He said to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Samuel told him everything, hiding nothing from him. And Eli said,
        \u201CIt is the Lord; may He do what seems good to Him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now Samuel grew; and the Lord was with him and He let none of his
        words fail [to be fulfilled]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And all Israel from Dan [in the north] to Beersheba [in the south]
        knew that Samuel was appointed as a prophet of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And the Lord continued to appear in Shiloh, for the Lord revealed
        Himself to Samuel in Shiloh by the word of the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Philistines Take the Ark in Victory'
      title: Philistines Take the Ark in Victory
      number: 1
      content: '  And the word of [the Lord through] Samuel came to all Israel. Now
        Israel went out to meet the Philistines in battle and they camped beside
        Ebenezer while the Philistines camped at Aphek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Philistines assembled in battle formation to meet Israel, and
        when the battle was over, Israel was defeated by the Philistines, who killed
        about four thousand men on the battlefield. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When the people (soldiers) came into the camp, the elders of Israel
        said, \u201CWhy has the Lord defeated us today before the Philistines? Let
        us bring the ark of the covenant of the Lord here from Shiloh, so that He
        may come among us and save us from the hand of our enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the people sent word to Shiloh, and from there they carried the
        ark of the covenant of the Lord of hosts who sits above the cherubim; and
        the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were with the ark of the covenant
        of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So it happened that as the ark of the covenant of the Lord came into
        the camp, all [the people of] Israel shouted with a great shout, and the
        earth resounded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When the Philistines heard the noise of the shout, they said, \u201CWhat
        does the noise of this great shout in the camp of the Hebrews mean?\u201D
        Then they understood that the ark of the Lord had come into the camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Philistines were afraid, for they said, \u201CGod has come into
        the camp.\u201D And they said, \u201CWoe [disaster is coming] to us! For
        nothing like this has happened before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Woe to us! Who will rescue us from the hand of these mighty gods?
        These are the gods who struck the Egyptians with all kinds of plagues in
        the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Take courage, and be men, O Philistines, so that you do not become
        servants to the Hebrews, as they have been servants to you; act like men
        and fight!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the Philistines fought; Israel was defeated and every man fled
        to his tent. It was a very great defeat, for thirty thousand foot soldiers
        of Israel fell. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Also the ark of God was taken; and the two sons of Eli, Hophni and
        Phinehas, were killed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now a man [from the tribe] of Benjamin ran from the battle line and
        came to Shiloh that same day with his clothes torn and dust on his head [as
        signs of mourning over the disaster]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When he arrived, Eli was sitting on his seat by the road, keeping
        watch, because his heart was anxious about the ark of God. When the man arrived
        to report [the news] in the city, everyone in the city cried out [to God,
        for help]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When Eli heard the noise of the outcry, he asked, \u201CWhat is the
        noise of this uproar?\u201D And the man came hurriedly and told Eli. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now Eli was ninety-eight years old; his eyes were dim so that he
        could not see. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The man said to Eli, \u201CI have come from the battle line. Indeed,
        I escaped from the battle line today.\u201D Eli said, \u201CHow did things
        go, my son?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The messenger replied, \u201CIsrael has fled before the Philistines
        and there has also been a great slaughter among the people. Also your two
        sons, Hophni and Phinehas, are dead, and the ark of God has been taken.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When he mentioned the ark of God, Eli fell off the seat backwards
        by the side of the [city] gate. His neck was broken and he died, for he was
        old and heavy. He had judged Israel for forty years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now his daughter-in-law, Phinehas\u2019 wife, was pregnant, and was
        about to give birth; so when she heard the news that the ark of God had been
        taken and that her father-in-law and her husband had died, she kneeled down
        and gave birth, because her [labor] pains began. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And about the time of her death [following the sudden birth] the
        women attending her said to her, \u201CDo not be afraid, for you have given
        birth to a son.\u201D But she did not answer or pay any attention. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And she named the boy Ichabod, saying, \u201CThe glory has left Israel,\u201D
        because the ark of God had been taken and because of [the deaths of] her
        father-in-law and her husband. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "She said, \u201CThe glory has left Israel, for the ark of God has
        been taken.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Capture of the Ark Provokes God'
      title: Capture of the Ark Provokes God
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the Philistines took the ark of God, and they brought it from
        Ebenezer to Ashdod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They took the ark of God and brought it into the house of Dagon and
        set it beside [the image of] Dagon [their chief idol]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When the people of Ashdod got up early the next day, behold, Dagon
        had fallen on his face on the ground before the ark of the Lord. So they
        took Dagon and returned him to his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But when they got up early the next morning, behold, Dagon had [again]
        fallen on his face on the ground before the ark of the Lord, and his head
        and both palms of his hands were [lying] cut off on the threshold; only the
        trunk [portion] of [the idol of] Dagon was left on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "This is the reason neither the priests of Dagon nor any who enter
        Dagon\u2019s house step on the threshold of Dagon in Ashdod to this day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the hand of the Lord was heavy on the people of Ashdod, and
        He caused them to be dumbfounded and struck them with tumors, both Ashdod
        and its territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When the men of Ashdod saw what had happened, they said, \u201CThe
        ark of the God of Israel must not remain with us, for His hand is heavy on
        us and on Dagon our god.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So they sent word and gathered all the lords (governors) of the Philistines
        to them and said, \u201CWhat shall we do with the ark of the God of Israel?\u201D
        They answered, \u201CLet the ark of the God of Israel be brought around to
        Gath.\u201D So they took the ark of the God of Israel there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But it happened that after they had taken it to Gath, the hand of
        the Lord was against the city, causing an extremely great panic [because
        of the deaths from the plague], for He struck the people of the city, both
        young and old, and tumors broke out on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they sent the ark of God to Ekron. And as the ark of God came
        to Ekron, the Ekronites cried out, \u201CThey have brought the ark of the
        God of Israel [from Gath] to us, to kill us and our people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So they sent word and gathered all the lords of the Philistines and
        said, \u201CSend away the ark of the God of Israel; let it be returned to
        its own place, so that it will not kill us and our people.\u201D For there
        was a deadly panic throughout the city; the hand of God was very heavy (severe)
        there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The men who had not died were stricken with tumors and the cry of
        the city [for help] went up to heaven.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Returned to Israel'
      title: The Ark Returned to Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the ark of the Lord had been in the country of the Philistines
        for seven months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Philistines called for the priests and the diviners (seers),
        saying, \u201CWhat shall we do with the ark of the Lord? Let us know how
        we can send it back to its place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said, \u201CIf you send away the ark of the God of Israel, do
        not send it empty [without a gift]; but be sure to return [it] to Him [together
        with] a guilt offering. Then you will be healed, and it will be known to
        you why His hand is not removed from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then they said, \u201CWhat shall the guilt offering be which we shall
        return to Him?\u201D They answered, \u201CFive golden tumors and five golden
        mice, according to the number of the lords (governors) of the Philistines,
        for one plague was on all of you and on your lords. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So you shall make replicas of your tumors and of your mice that ravage
        the land, and give glory to the God of Israel; perhaps He will lighten His
        hand [of judgment] on you and your gods and your land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Why then do you harden your hearts [allowing pride to cause your
        downfall] just as the Egyptians and Pharaoh hardened their hearts? When He
        had severely dealt with them and mocked them, did they not allow the people
        [of Israel] to go, and they departed? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now then, make a new cart and prepare two milk cows on which a yoke
        has never been placed; and hitch the cows to the cart and take their calves
        back home, away from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then take the ark of the Lord and put it on the cart; and put the
        articles of gold which you are returning to Him as a guilt offering in a
        box beside it. Then send it away [without a driver]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But watch, if it goes up by the way of its own territory to Beth-shemesh,
        then [you will know that] He has done us this great evil. But if not, then
        we will know that it was not His hand that struck us; this disaster happened
        to us by chance.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the men did so, and took two milk cows and hitched them to the
        cart, and corralled their calves at home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They put the ark of the Lord on the cart, and the box containing
        the golden mice and the replicas of their tumors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the cows went straight toward Beth-shemesh along the highway,
        lowing as they went, and did not turn away to the right or the left. And
        the Philistine lords (governors) followed them to the border of Beth-shemesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the men of Beth-shemesh were gathering their wheat harvest in
        the valley, and they looked up and saw the ark and rejoiced to see it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The cart came into the field of Joshua of Beth-shemesh and stopped
        there. A large stone was there; and the men split up the wood of the cart
        [for firewood] and offered the cows as a burnt offering to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Levites had taken down the ark of the Lord and the box beside
        it, in which were the articles of gold, and put them on the large stone.
        And the men of Beth-shemesh offered burnt offerings and made sacrifices that
        day to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When the five lords of the Philistines saw what happened, they returned
        to Ekron that day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'These are the golden tumors which the Philistines returned as a guilt
        offering to the Lord: one for Ashdod, one for Gaza, one for Ashkelon, one
        for Gath and one for Ekron [the five chief cities of the Philistines]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'also the golden mice, according to the number of all the cities of
        the Philistines belonging to the five lords, both fortified cities and [unwalled]
        country villages. The large stone on which the Levites set the ark of the
        Lord  remains a witness to this day in the field of Joshua of Beth-shemesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The Lord struck down some of the men of Beth-shemesh because they
        had looked into the ark of the Lord. He struck down 50,070 men among the
        people, and the people mourned because the Lord had struck the people with
        a great slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The men of Beth-shemesh said, \u201CWho is able to stand before the
        Lord, this holy God? And to whom shall He go up from us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So they sent messengers to the residents of Kiriath-jearim, saying,
        \u201CThe Philistines have returned the ark of the Lord. Come down and take
        it up to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rescue from the Philistines'
      title: Rescue from the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: '  So the men of Kiriath-jearim came and took up the ark of the Lord
        and brought it into the house of Abinadab on the hill, and they consecrated
        Eleazar his son to care for the ark of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And from that day the ark remained in Kiriath-jearim for a very long
        time, for it was twenty years [until the reign of King David]; and all the
        house of Israel lamented (wailed) and grieved after the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Samuel said to all the house of Israel, \u201CIf you are returning
        to the Lord with all your heart, remove the foreign gods and the Ashtaroth
        (pagan goddesses) from among you and direct your hearts to the Lord and serve
        Him only; and He will rescue you from the hand of the Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the Israelites removed the Baals and the Ashtaroth and served
        the Lord alone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Samuel said, \u201CGather all Israel together at Mizpah and I will
        pray to the Lord for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So they gathered at Mizpah, and drew water and poured it out before
        the Lord, and fasted on that day and said there, \u201CWe have sinned against
        the Lord.\u201D And Samuel judged the Israelites at Mizpah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now when the Philistines heard that the Israelites had gathered at
        Mizpah, the lords (governors) of the Philistines went up against Israel.
        And when the Israelites heard it, they were afraid of the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the sons of Israel said to Samuel, \u201CDo not cease to cry
        out to the Lord our God for us, so that He may save us from the hand of the
        Philistines.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Samuel took a nursing lamb and offered it as a whole burnt offering
        to the Lord; and Samuel cried out to the Lord for Israel and the Lord answered
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As Samuel was offering up the burnt offering, the Philistines approached
        for the battle against Israel. Then the Lord thundered with a great voice
        that day against the Philistines and threw them into confusion, and they
        were defeated and fled before Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the men of Israel came out of Mizpah and pursued the Philistines,
        and struck them down as far as [the territory] below Beth-car.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Samuel took a stone and set it between Mizpah and Shen, and
        he named it Ebenezer (stone of help), saying, \u201CThus far the Lord has
        helped us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the Philistines were subdued and they did not come anymore into
        Israelite territory. And the hand of the Lord was against the Philistines
        all the days of Samuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Samuel\u2019s Ministry"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s Ministry"
      number: 14
      content: "The cities which the Philistines had taken from Israel were restored
        to Israel, from Ekron to Gath; and Israel recovered the cities\u2019 territory
        from the Philistines. Also there was peace between Israel and the Amorites.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now Samuel judged Israel all the days of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He used to go annually on a circuit to Bethel, Gilgal, and Mizpah,
        and he judged Israel in all these places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then he would return to Ramah, because his home was there; and there
        he judged Israel, and there he built an altar to the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Demands a King'
      title: Israel Demands a King
      number: 1
      content: '  And it came about when Samuel was old that he appointed his sons
        as judges over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now the name of his firstborn was Joel, and the name of his second,
        Abijah; they were judging in Beersheba. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'His sons, however, did not walk in his ways, but turned aside after
        dishonest gain, took bribes, and perverted justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then all the elders of Israel gathered together and came to Samuel
        at Ramah '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and said to him, \u201CLook, you have grown old, and your sons do
        not walk in your ways. Now appoint us a king to judge us [and rule over us]
        like all the other nations.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But their demand displeased Samuel when they said, \u201CGive us
        a king to judge and rule over us.\u201D So Samuel prayed to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Lord said to Samuel, \u201CListen to the voice of the people
        in regard to all that they say to you, for they have not rejected you, but
        they have rejected Me from being King over them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Like all the deeds which they have done since the day that I brought
        them up from Egypt even to this day\u2014in that they have abandoned (rejected)
        Me and served other gods\u2014so they are doing to you also. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Warning concerning a King'
      title: Warning concerning a King
      number: 9
      content: "So now listen to their voice; only solemnly warn them and tell them
        the ways of the king who will reign over them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Samuel told all the words of the Lord to the people who were asking
        him for a king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said, \u201CThese will be the ways of the king who will reign
        over you: he will take your sons and appoint them for himself to his chariots
        and among his horsemen and they will run before his chariots. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He will appoint them for himself to be commanders over thousands
        and over fifties, and some to do his plowing and to reap his harvest and
        to make his implements of war and equipment for his chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He will take your daughters to be perfumers, cooks, and bakers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He will take the best of your fields, your vineyards, and your olive
        groves, and give them to his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He will take a tenth of your grain and of your vineyards and give
        it to his officers and to his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He will take your male servants and your female servants and your
        best young men and your donkeys and use them for his work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He will take a tenth of your flocks, and you yourselves shall be
        his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then you will cry out on that day because of your king whom you have
        chosen for yourselves, but the Lord will not answer you on that day [because
        you have rejected Him as King].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Nevertheless, the people refused to listen to the voice of Samuel,
        and they said, \u201CNo, but there shall be a king over us, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "so that we too may be like all the nations [around us], that our
        king may judge [and govern] us and go out before us and fight our battles.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Samuel had heard all the words of the people and repeated them to
        the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the Lord said to Samuel, \u201CListen to their request and appoint
        a king for them.\u201D So Samuel said to the men of Israel, \u201CGo, each
        man to his own city.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Saul\u2019s Search"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Search"
      number: 1
      content: '  There was a man of [the tribe of] Benjamin whose name was Kish
        the son of Abiel, the son of Zeror, the son of Becorath, the son of Aphiah,
        a Benjamite, a mighty man of influence and wealth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Kish had a son named Saul, a choice and handsome man; among the sons
        of Israel there was not a man more handsome than he. From his shoulders and
        up he was [a head] taller than any of the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now the donkeys of Kish, Saul\u2019s father, had wandered off and
        were lost. Kish said to his son Saul, \u201CPlease take one of the servants
        with you and arise, go look for the donkeys.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they passed through the hill country of Ephraim and the land
        of Shalishah, but did not find them. Then they passed through the land of
        Shaalim, but they were not there and the land of the Benjamites, but they
        [still] did not find them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When they came to the land of Zuph, Saul said to his servant who
        was with him, \u201CCome, let us return, otherwise my father will stop worrying
        about the donkeys and become anxious about us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The servant said to him, \u201CLook here, in this city there is a
        man of God, and the man is held in honor; everything that he says comes true.
        Now let us go there; perhaps he can advise us about our journey [and tell
        us where we should go].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Saul said to his servant, \u201CBut look, if we go [to see him],
        what shall we bring to the man? For the bread from our sacks is gone and
        there is no gift to bring to the man of God. What do we have [to offer]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The servant replied again to Saul, \u201CHere in my hand I have a
        quarter of a shekel of silver; I will give that to the man of God, and he
        will advise us as to [where we should go on] our journey [to find the donkeys].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "(Formerly in Israel, when a man went to inquire of God, he would
        say, \u201CCome, let us go to the seer\u201D; for he who is called a prophet
        today was formerly called a seer.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Saul said to his servant, \u201CWell said; come, let us go.\u201D
        So they went to the city where the man of God was living.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "As they went up the hill to the city, they met some young women going
        out to draw water, and said to them, \u201CIs the seer (prophet) here?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They answered them, \u201CHe is; look, he is ahead of you. Hurry
        now, for he has come into the city today because the people have a sacrifice
        on the high place today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As you enter the city you will find him before he goes up to the
        high place to eat, for the people will not eat until he comes, because he
        must ask the blessing on the sacrifice; afterward, those who are invited
        will eat. So go up now, for about now you will find him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: God\u2019s Choice for King"
      title: "God\u2019s Choice for King"
      number: 14
      content: 'So they went up to the city. And as they came into the city, there
        was Samuel coming out toward them to go up to the high place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now a day before Saul came, the Lord had informed Samuel [of this],
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAbout this time tomorrow I will send you a man from the land
        of Benjamin, and you shall anoint him as leader over My people Israel; and
        he will save My people from the hand of the Philistines. For I have looked
        upon [the distress of] My people, because their cry [for help] has come to
        Me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When Samuel saw Saul, the Lord said to him, \u201CThere is the man
        of whom I spoke to you. This one shall rule over My people [as their king].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Saul approached Samuel in the [city] gate and said, \u201CPlease
        tell me where the seer\u2019s house is.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Samuel answered Saul, \u201CI am the seer. Go on ahead of me to the
        high place, for you shall eat with me today; and in the morning I will let
        you go, and will tell you all that is on your mind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "As for your donkeys which were lost three days ago, do not be concerned
        about them, for they have been found. And for whom are all things that are
        desirable in Israel? Are they not for you and for all your father\u2019s
        household (family)?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Saul replied, \u201CAm I not a Benjamite, of the smallest of the
        tribes of Israel? And is not my family the smallest of all the families of
        the tribe of Benjamin? Why then have you spoken this way to me [as if I were
        very important]?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Samuel took Saul and his servant and brought them into the hall
        [at the high place] and gave them a place [to sit] at the head of the persons\u2014about
        thirty men\u2014who were invited [while the rest ate outside]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Samuel said to the cook, \u201CBring the [priests\u2019] portion
        that I gave you, regarding which I told you, \u2018Set it aside.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the cook lifted up the leg (thigh) with the meat that was on
        it [indicating that it was the priest\u2019s honored portion] and placed
        it before Saul. Samuel said, \u201CHere is what has been reserved [for you].
        Set it before you and eat, because it has been kept for you until the appointed
        time, ever since I invited the people.\u201D So Saul ate with Samuel that
        day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When they came down from the high place into the city, Samuel spoke
        with Saul on the roof [of his house]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "They got up early [the next day]; and at dawn Samuel called Saul
        [who was sleeping] on the roof, saying, \u201CGet up, so that I may send
        you on your way.\u201D Saul got up, and both he and Samuel went outside. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "As they were going down to the outskirts of the city, Samuel said
        to Saul, \u201CTell the servant to go on ahead of us so that he may pass
        by but you stand still now so that I may proclaim the word of God to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul among Prophets'
      title: Saul among Prophets
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Samuel took the flask of oil and poured it on Saul\u2019s
        head, kissed him, and said, \u201CHas the Lord not anointed you as ruler
        over His inheritance (Israel)? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When you leave me today, you will meet two men beside Rachel\u2019s
        tomb in the territory of Benjamin at Zelzah; they will say to you, \u2018The
        donkeys you went to look for have been found. And your father has stopped
        caring about them and is worried about you, saying, \u201CWhat shall I do
        about my son?\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then you will go on further from there, and you will come to the
        terebinth tree of Tabor, and three men going up to [sacrifice to] God at
        Bethel will meet you there, one carrying three young goats, another carrying
        three loaves of bread, and another carrying a jug of wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They will greet you and give you two loaves of bread, which you will
        accept from their hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'After that you will come to the hill of God where the garrison of
        the Philistines is; and when you come there to the city, you will meet a
        group of prophets coming down from the high place [of worship] with harp,
        tambourine, flute, and lyre before them, and they will be prophesying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the Spirit of the Lord will come upon you mightily, and you
        will prophesy with them, and you will be changed into another man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When these signs come to you, do for yourself whatever the situation
        requires, for God is with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You shall go down ahead of me to Gilgal; and behold, I will be coming
        down to you to offer burnt offerings and to sacrifice peace offerings. You
        shall wait seven days until I come to you and show you what you must do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then it happened when Saul turned his back to leave Samuel, God changed
        his heart; and all those signs came to pass that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they came to the hill [Gibeah], behold, a group of prophets
        met him; and the Spirit of God came on him mightily, and he prophesied [under
        divine guidance] among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now when all who knew Saul previously saw that he actually prophesied
        now [by inspiration] with the prophets, the people said one to another, \u201CWhat
        has happened to [Saul, who is nobody but] the son of Kish? Is Saul also among
        the prophets?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And a man from there answered, \u201CBut who is the father of the
        others?\u201D So it became a proverb, \u201CIs Saul also among the prophets?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When Saul had finished prophesying, he went to the high place [of
        worship].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Saul\u2019s uncle said to him and to his servant, \u201CWhere did
        you go?\u201D And Saul said, \u201CTo look for the donkeys. And when we saw
        that they were nowhere to be found, we went to Samuel [for help].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Saul\u2019s uncle said, \u201CPlease tell me, what did Samuel say
        to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Saul Publicly Chosen King'
      title: Saul Publicly Chosen King
      number: 16
      content: "And Saul said to his uncle, \u201CHe told us plainly that the donkeys
        had been found.\u201D But he did not tell him about the matter of the kingdom
        which Samuel had mentioned.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Samuel called the people together to the Lord at Mizpah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and he said to Israel, \u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel,
        \u2018It was I who brought Israel up from Egypt, and I rescued you from the
        hand of the Egyptians and from all the kingdoms that were oppressing you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But today you have rejected your God, who Himself saves you from
        all your disasters and distresses; yet you have said, \u2018No! Set a king
        over us.\u2019 Now then, present yourselves before the Lord by your tribes
        and by your families (clans).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And when Samuel brought all the tribes of Israel near, the tribe
        of Benjamin was chosen by lot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then he brought the tribe of Benjamin near by their families, and
        the family of Matri was chosen by lot. And Saul the son of Kish was chosen
        by lot; but when they looked for him, he could not be found. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So they inquired further of the Lord, \u201CHas the man come here
        yet?\u201D And the Lord answered, \u201CHe is there, hiding himself by the
        provisions and supplies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So they ran and took him from there, and when he stood among the
        people, he was taller than any of the people from his shoulders upward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Samuel said to all the people, \u201CDo you see him whom the Lord
        has chosen? For there is no one like him among all the people.\u201D So all
        the people shouted and said, \u201CLong live the king!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Samuel told the people the requirements of the kingdom, and
        wrote them in a book and placed it before the Lord. And Samuel sent all the
        people away, each one to his home. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Saul also went home to Gibeah; and the brave men whose hearts God
        had touched went with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But some worthless men said, \u201CHow can this man save and rescue
        us?\u201D And they regarded Saul with contempt and did not bring him a gift.
        But he ignored the insult and kept silent."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul Defeats the Ammonites'
      title: Saul Defeats the Ammonites
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Nahash the Ammonite [king] went up and besieged Jabesh-gilead;
        and all the men of Jabesh said to Nahash, \u201CMake a treaty [of peace]
        with us and we will serve you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Nahash the Ammonite told them, \u201CI will make a treaty with
        you on this condition, that I will gouge out the right eye of every one of
        you, and make it a disgrace upon all Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The elders of Jabesh said to Nahash, \u201CGive us seven days so
        that we may send messengers throughout the territory of Israel. Then, if
        there is no one to save us, we will come out [and surrender] to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the messengers came to Gibeah of Saul and told the news to the
        people; and all the people raised their voices and wept aloud.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now Saul was coming out of the field behind the oxen, and he said,
        \u201CWhat is the matter with the people that they are weeping?\u201D So
        they told him about the report of the men of Jabesh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The Spirit of God came upon Saul mightily when he heard these words,
        and he became extremely angry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He took a team of oxen and cut them in pieces, and sent them throughout
        the territory of Israel by the hand of messengers, saying, \u201CWhoever
        does not come out to follow Saul and Samuel, the same shall be done to his
        oxen.\u201D Then fear of the Lord fell on the people, and they came out [united]
        as one man [with one purpose]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He assembled and counted them at Bezek; and the sons of Israel numbered
        300,000, and the men of Judah 30,000. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They said to the messengers who had come, \u201CYou shall say to
        the men of Jabesh-gilead: \u2018Tomorrow, by the time the sun is hot, you
        will have help [against the Ammonites].\u2019\u2009\u201D So the messengers
        came and reported this to the men of Jabesh; and they were overjoyed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the men of Jabesh said [to Nahash the Ammonite], \u201CTomorrow
        we will come out to you [to surrender], and you may do to us whatever seems
        good to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The next morning Saul put the men into three companies; and they
        entered the [Ammonites\u2019] camp during the [darkness of the early] morning
        watch and killed the Ammonites until the heat of the day; and the survivors
        were scattered, and no two of them were left together.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The people said to Samuel, \u201CWho is the one who said, \u2018Shall
        Saul reign over us?\u2019 Bring the men, and we will put them to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But Saul said, \u201CNo man shall be put to death this day, for today
        the Lord has brought victory to Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Samuel said to the people, \u201CCome, let us go to Gilgal and there
        restore the kingdom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So all the people went to Gilgal, and there they made Saul king before
        the Lord in Gilgal. There they also sacrificed peace offerings before the
        Lord; and there Saul and all the men of Israel rejoiced greatly.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Samuel Addresses Israel'
      title: Samuel Addresses Israel
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Samuel said to all Israel, \u201CBehold, I have listened to
        your voice in everything that you have said to me and have appointed a king
        over you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And now, here is the king walking before you. As for me, I am old
        and gray, and here are my sons with you. I have walked before you from my
        childhood to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Here I am; testify against me before the Lord and [Saul] His anointed
        [if I have done someone wrong]. Whose ox have I taken, or whose donkey have
        I taken, or whom have I exploited? Whom have I oppressed or from whose hand
        have I taken a bribe to blind my eyes [to the truth]? [Tell me and] I will
        restore it to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They said, \u201CYou have not exploited us or oppressed us or taken
        anything at all from a man\u2019s hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Samuel said to them, \u201CThe Lord is a witness against you, and
        [Saul] His anointed is a witness this day that you have not found anything
        in my hand.\u201D And they answered, \u201CHe is a witness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Samuel said to the people, \u201CIt is the Lord who appointed
        Moses and Aaron and brought your fathers (ancestors) up from the land of
        Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now then, take your stand, so that I may plead and contend with you
        before the Lord concerning all the righteous acts of the Lord which He did
        for you and for your fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When Jacob [and his sons] had come into Egypt [and later when the
        Egyptians oppressed them] and your fathers cried out to the Lord, then the
        Lord sent Moses and Aaron who brought your fathers out of Egypt and settled
        them in this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But when they forgot the Lord their God, He sold them into the hand
        of Sisera, commander of Hazor\u2019s army, and into the hand of the Philistines
        and of the king of Moab, and they fought against them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "They cried out to the Lord, saying, \u2018We have sinned because
        we have abandoned (rejected) the Lord and have served the Baals and the Ashtaroth;
        but now rescue us from the hands of our enemies, and we will serve You.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The King Confirmed'
      title: The King Confirmed
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the Lord sent Jerubbaal (Gideon) and Bedan and Jephthah and
        Samuel, and He rescued you from the hand of your enemies on every side, and
        you lived in security.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But when you saw that Nahash king of the Ammonites had come against
        you, you said to me, \u2018No, but a king shall reign over us\u2019\u2014although
        the Lord your God was your King. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now therefore, here is [Saul] the king whom you have chosen, and
        for whom you asked; behold, the Lord has set a king over you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If you will fear the Lord [with awe and profound reverence] and serve
        Him and listen to His voice and not rebel against His commandment, then both
        you and your king will follow the Lord your God [and it will be well]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But if you do not listen to the Lord\u2019s voice, but rebel against
        His command, then the hand of the Lord will be against you [to punish you],
        as it was against your fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So now, take your stand and see this great thing which the Lord will
        do before your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Is it not [the beginning of the] wheat harvest today? I will call
        to the Lord and He will send thunder and rain; then you will know [without
        any doubt], and see that your evil which you have done is great in the sight
        of the Lord by asking for yourselves a king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Samuel called to the Lord [in prayer], and He sent thunder and
        rain that day; and all the people greatly feared the Lord and Samuel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then all the people said to Samuel, \u201CPray to the Lord your God
        for your servants, so that we will not die, for we have added to all our
        sins this evil\u2014to ask for a king for ourselves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Samuel said to the people, \u201CDo not be afraid. You have [indeed]
        done all this evil; yet do not turn away from following the Lord, but serve
        the Lord with all your heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You must not turn away, for then you would go after futile things
        which cannot profit or rescue, because they are futile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The Lord will not abandon His people for His great name\u2019s sake,
        because the Lord has been pleased to make you a people for Himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Moreover, as for me, far be it from me that I should sin against
        the Lord by ceasing to pray for you; but I will instruct you in the good
        and right way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Only fear the Lord [with awe and profound reverence] and serve Him
        faithfully with all your heart; for consider what great things He has done
        for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But if you still do evil, both you and your king will be swept away
        [to destruction].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: War with the Philistines'
      title: War with the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: '  Saul was thirty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned
        forty-two years over Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Saul chose for himself 3,000 men of Israel; of whom 2,000 were with
        him in Michmash and in the hill country of Bethel, while 1,000 were with
        Jonathan at Gibeah of Benjamin. But he sent the rest of the people away,
        each one to his own tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jonathan attacked and defeated the Philistine garrison which was
        at Geba, and the Philistines heard about it. Then Saul blew the trumpet throughout
        the land, saying, \u201CLet the Hebrews hear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'All Israel heard that Saul had defeated the Philistine garrison,
        and also that Israel had become despicable to the Philistines. And the people
        were summoned to join Saul at Gilgal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the Philistines gathered to fight against Israel, 30,000 chariots
        and 6,000 horsemen, and troops in multitude, like sand on the seashore. They
        came up and camped at Michmash, east of Beth-aven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When the men of Israel saw that they were in a tight situation (for
        their troops were hard-pressed), they hid in caves, in thickets, in cellars,
        and in [dry] cisterns (pits). '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Also some of the Hebrews had crossed the [river] Jordan to the land
        of Gad and Gilead. As for Saul, he was still in Gilgal, and all the people
        followed him, trembling [in fear and anticipation].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now Saul waited seven days, according to the appointed time which
        Samuel had set, but Samuel had not come to Gilgal; and the people were scattering
        away from Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Saul said, \u201CBring me the burnt offering and the peace offerings.\u201D
        And he offered the burnt offering [which he was forbidden to do]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As soon as he finished offering the burnt offering, Samuel finally
        came; Saul went out to meet and to welcome him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Samuel said, \u201CWhat have you done?\u201D Saul said, \u201CSince
        I saw that the people were scattering away from me, and that you did not
        come within the appointed time, and that the Philistines were assembling
        at Michmash, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "therefore, I said, \u2018Now the Philistines will come down against
        me at Gilgal, and I have not asked for the Lord\u2019s favor [by making supplication
        to Him].\u2019 So I forced myself to offer the burnt offering.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Samuel said to Saul, \u201CYou have acted foolishly; you have not
        kept the commandment of the Lord your God, which He commanded you, for [if
        you had obeyed] the Lord would have established your kingdom over Israel
        forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But now your kingdom shall not endure. The Lord has sought out for
        Himself a man (David) after His own heart, and the Lord has appointed him
        as leader and ruler over His people, because you have not kept (obeyed) what
        the Lord commanded you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Samuel arose and went up from Gilgal to Gibeah of Benjamin.
        And Saul assembled and counted the people who were still with him, [only]
        about six hundred [fighting] men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Saul and his son Jonathan and the people with them were staying in
        Geba of Benjamin, while the Philistines camped at Michmash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the raiding party came from the Philistine camp in three companies:
        one company turned toward Ophrah, to the land of Shual, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'another company turned toward Beth-horon, and another toward the
        border overlooking the Valley of Zeboim toward the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now no blacksmith (metal-worker) could be found in all the land of
        Israel, for the Philistines said, \u201COtherwise the Hebrews will make swords
        or spears.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So all [the men of] Israel went down to the Philistines, each to
        get his plowshare, pick, axe, or sickle sharpened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The fee [for sharpening] was a pim (two-thirds of a shekel) for the
        plowshares, the picks, the pitchforks, and the axes, and to straighten the
        goads (cattle prods). '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So it came about on the day of battle that neither sword nor spear
        was found in the hands of any of the people who were with Saul and Jonathan;
        but Saul and Jonathan his son had them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And the garrison of the Philistines went out to the pass at Michmash.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jonathan\u2019s Victory"
      title: "Jonathan\u2019s Victory"
      number: 1
      content: "  One day Jonathan the son of Saul said to his young armor bearer,
        \u201CCome, let us go over to the Philistine garrison on the other side.\u201D
        But he did not tell his father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Saul was staying in the outskirts of Gibeah under a pomegranate tree
        in Migron; and with him were about six hundred men, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and Ahijah the son of Ichabod\u2019s brother Ahitub the son of Phinehas,
        the son of Eli, the Lord\u2019s priest at Shiloh, was wearing the ephod.
        And the people did not know that Jonathan had gone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Between the passes by which Jonathan sought to cross over to get
        to the Philistine garrison, there was a rocky crag on the one side and a
        rocky crag on the other side; one [crag] was named Bozez, and the other,
        Seneh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The one crag was on the north in front of Michmash, and the other
        on the south in front of Geba.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jonathan said to his young armor bearer, \u201CCome, let us cross
        over to the garrison of these uncircumcised men; it may be that the Lord
        will work for us. For there is nothing to prevent the Lord from saving, whether
        by many or by few.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And his armor bearer said to him, \u201CDo everything that is in
        your heart (mind); here I am with you in whatever you think [best].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jonathan said, \u201CSee now, we are going to cross over to the [Philistine]
        men and reveal ourselves to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If they say to us, \u2018Wait until we come to you,\u2019 then we
        will stand in our place and not go up to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But if they say, \u2018Come up to us,\u2019 we will go up, for the
        Lord has handed them over to us; and this shall be the sign to us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When both of them revealed themselves to the garrison of the Philistines,
        the Philistines said, \u201CLook, the Hebrews are coming out of the holes
        where they have hidden themselves.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So the men of the garrison responded to Jonathan and his armor bearer,
        \u201CCome up to us and we will tell you something.\u201D Jonathan said to
        his armor bearer, \u201CClimb up after me, for the Lord has given them into
        the hands of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Jonathan climbed up on his hands and feet, his armor bearer
        following after him. The enemy fell before Jonathan [in combat], and his
        armor bearer killed some of them after him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'That first slaughter which Jonathan and his armor bearer made was
        about twenty men within about half a [plow] furrow in a plot of land [the
        area of which a yoke of oxen could plow in a day]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And there was trembling in the [Philistine] camp, in the field, and
        among all the people; even the garrison and the raiding party trembled [in
        fear], and the earth quaked and it became a trembling and terror from God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Saul\u2019s watchmen in Gibeah of Benjamin looked, and behold, the
        multitude melted away and they went here and there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul said to the people with him, \u201CTake a count and see
        who has left us.\u201D When they had taken a count, behold, Jonathan and
        his armor bearer were missing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Saul said to Ahijah [the priest], \u201CBring the ark of God here.\u201D
        For at that time the ark of God was with the sons of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "While Saul talked to the priest, the commotion in the Philistine
        camp continued and increased, so Saul said to the priest, \u201CWithdraw
        your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Saul and all the people who were with him rallied and went into
        the battle; and behold, every [Philistine] man\u2019s sword was against his
        companion, in wild confusion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the Hebrews who were with the Philistines previously, who went
        up with them all around in the camp, they also turned to be with the Israelites
        who were with Saul and Jonathan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When all the men of Israel who had hidden themselves in the hill
        country of Ephraim heard that the Philistines had fled, they too pursued
        them closely in the battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: "23: Saul\u2019s Foolish Order"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Foolish Order"
      number: 23
      content: 'So the Lord saved Israel that day, and the battle spread beyond Beth-aven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But the men of Israel were hard-pressed that day, because Saul had
        put the people under a curse, saying, \u201CCursed be the man who eats food
        before evening, and before I have taken vengeance on my enemies.\u201D So
        none of the people ate any food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'All the people of the land came to a forest, and there was honey
        on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When the people entered the forest, the honey was dripping, but no
        man put his hand to his mouth [to taste it], because the people feared the
        oath [of Saul]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But Jonathan had not heard when his father put the people under the
        oath. So he put out the end of the staff that was in his hand and dipped
        it into a honeycomb, and then he put his hand to his mouth, and his energy
        was restored. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "But one of the people told him, \u201CYour father strictly put the
        people under an oath, saying, \u2018Cursed be the man who eats food today.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        And the people were exhausted [and hungry]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Jonathan said, \u201CMy father has troubled the land [with his
        foolish curse]. See how my energy is restored because I tasted a little of
        this honey. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "How much better [it would have been] if only the people had eaten
        freely today from the spoil of their enemies which they found! For now the
        slaughter among the Philistines has not been great.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'They struck the Philistines that day from Michmash to Aijalon. And
        the people were very tired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '[When night came and the oath ended] the people rushed greedily upon
        the spoil. They took sheep, oxen, and calves, and slaughtered them on the
        ground; and they ate them [raw] with the blood [still in them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Saul was told, \u201CLook, the people are sinning against the
        Lord by eating [the meat] with the blood.\u201D And he said, \u201CYou have
        violated [the Law] and acted treacherously; roll a large stone to me today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Saul said, \u201CSpread out among the people and tell them, \u2018Each
        one of you bring me his ox or his sheep, and butcher it [properly] here and
        eat; and do not sin against the Lord by eating [the meat with] the blood.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        So that night each one brought his ox with him and butchered it there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And Saul built an altar to the Lord; it was the first altar that
        he built to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CLet us go down after the Philistines by night
        and plunder them until the morning light, and let us not leave a man of them
        [alive].\u201D They said, \u201CDo whatever seems good to you.\u201D Then
        the priest said, \u201CLet us approach God here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Saul asked [counsel] of God, \u201CShall I go down after the Philistines?
        Will You hand them over to Israel?\u201D But He did not answer him that day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CCome here, all you who are leaders of the people,
        and let us find out how this sin [causing God\u2019s silence] happened today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "For as the Lord lives, who saves Israel, for even if the guilt is
        in my son Jonathan, he shall most certainly die.\u201D But not one of all
        the people answered him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then he said to all the Israelites, \u201CYou shall be on one side;
        I and my son Jonathan will be on the other side.\u201D The people said to
        Saul, \u201CDo what seems good to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Therefore, Saul said to the Lord, the God of Israel, \u201CGive a
        perfect lot [identifying the transgressor].\u201D Then Saul and Jonathan
        were selected [by lot], but the other men went free. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Saul said, \u201CCast [lots] between me and my son Jonathan.\u201D
        And Jonathan was selected.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Saul said to Jonathan, \u201CTell me what you have done.\u201D So
        Jonathan told him, \u201CI tasted a little honey with the end of the staff
        that was in my hand. Here I am, I must die!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Saul answered, \u201CMay God do so [to me], and more also [if I do
        not keep my word], for you shall most certainly die, Jonathan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "But the people said to Saul, \u201CMust Jonathan, who has brought
        about this great victory in Israel, be put to death? Far from it! As the
        Lord lives, not one hair of his head shall fall to the ground, for he has
        worked with God this day.\u201D So the people rescued Jonathan and he was
        not put to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: Constant Warfare'
      title: Constant Warfare
      number: 46
      content: 'Then Saul stopped pursuing the Philistines, and the Philistines went
        to their own place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'When Saul assumed control of the kingdom of Israel, he fought against
        all his enemies on every side: Moab, the sons (descendants) of Ammon, Edom,
        the kings of Zobah, and the Philistines. Wherever he turned, he inflicted
        punishment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'He acted valiantly and defeated the Amalekites, and rescued Israel
        from the hands of those who had plundered them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Now Saul\u2019s sons were Jonathan, Ishvi, and Malchi-shua. The names
        of his two daughters were these: the name of the firstborn was Merab, and
        the name of the younger, Michal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "The name of Saul\u2019s wife was Ahinoam the daughter of Ahimaaz.
        The commander of his army was named Abner, the son of Ner, Saul\u2019s uncle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Kish was the father of Saul, and Ner the father of Abner was the
        son of Abiel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: Now the war against the Philistines was severe (brutal, relentless)
        all the days of Saul; and whenever Saul saw any mighty or courageous man,
        he recruited him for his staff.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Saul\u2019s Disobedience"
      title: "Saul\u2019s Disobedience"
      number: 1
      content: "  Samuel said to Saul, \u201CThe Lord sent me to anoint you king
        over His people Israel. Now listen and pay close attention to the words of
        the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts (armies), \u2018I will punish Amalek
        for what he did to Israel, how he set himself against him on the way when
        Israel came up from Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now go and strike Amalek and completely destroy everything that they
        have; do not spare them, but kill both man and woman, child and infant, ox
        and sheep, camel and donkey.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Saul summoned the people and numbered them at Telaim\u2014200,000
        foot soldiers and 10,000 men of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Saul came to the city of Amalek and set an ambush in the valley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Saul said to the Kenites, \u201CGo, leave, go down from the Amalekites,
        so that I do not destroy you along with them; for you showed kindness to
        all the Israelites when they went up from Egypt.\u201D So the Kenites departed
        from among the Amalekites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Saul defeated the Amalekites, from Havilah as far as Shur, which
        is east of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He captured Agag the king of the Amalekites alive, though he totally
        destroyed all [the rest of] the people with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Samuel Rebukes Saul'
      title: Samuel Rebukes Saul
      number: 9
      content: 'Saul and the people spared Agag and the best of the sheep, the oxen,
        the fatlings, the lambs, and everything that was good, and they were not
        willing to destroy them entirely; but everything that was undesirable or
        worthless they destroyed completely.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to Samuel, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI regret that I made Saul king, for he has turned away from
        following Me and has not carried out My commands.\u201D Samuel was angry
        [over Saul\u2019s failure] and he cried out to the Lord all night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When Samuel got up early in the morning to meet Saul, he was told,
        \u201CSaul came to Carmel, and behold, he set up for himself a monument [commemorating
        his victory], then he turned and went on and went down to Gilgal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Samuel came to Saul, and Saul said to him, \u201CBlessed are you
        of the Lord. I have carried out the command of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Samuel said, \u201CWhat then is this bleating of the sheep in
        my ears, and the lowing of the oxen which I hear?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Saul said, \u201CThey have brought them from the Amalekites, for
        the people spared the best of the sheep and oxen to sacrifice to the Lord
        your God; but the rest we have destroyed completely.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Samuel said to Saul, \u201CStop, and let me tell you what the
        Lord said to me last night.\u201D Saul said to him, \u201CSpeak.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Samuel said, \u201CIs it not true that even though you were small
        (insignificant) in your own eyes, you were made the head of the tribes of
        Israel? And the Lord anointed you king over Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and the Lord sent you on a mission, and said, \u2018Go, totally destroy
        the sinners, the Amalekites, and fight against them until they are eliminated.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Why did you not obey the voice of the Lord, but [instead] swooped
        down on the plunder [with shouts of victory] and did evil in the sight of
        the Lord?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Saul said to Samuel, \u201CI have obeyed the voice of the Lord, and
        have gone on the mission on which the Lord sent me, and have brought back
        Agag the king of Amalek, and have completely destroyed the Amalekites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But the people took some of the spoil, sheep and oxen, the best of
        the things [that were] to be totally destroyed, to sacrifice to the Lord
        your God at Gilgal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Samuel said,\u201CHas the Lord as great a delight in burnt offerings
        and sacrificesAs in obedience to the voice of the Lord?Behold, to obey is
        better than sacrifice,And to heed [is better] than the fat of rams.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For rebellion is as [serious as] the sin of divination (fortune-telling),And
        disobedience is as [serious as] false religion and idolatry.Because you have
        rejected the word of the Lord,He also has rejected you as king.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Saul said to Samuel, \u201CI have sinned; for I have transgressed
        the command of the Lord and your words, because I feared the people and obeyed
        their voice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now, please, pardon my sin and return with me, so that I may worship
        the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Samuel said to Saul, \u201CI will not return with you; for you
        have rejected the word of the Lord, and the Lord has rejected you from being
        king over Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'As Samuel turned to go [away], Saul grabbed the hem of his robe [to
        stop him], and it tore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So Samuel said to him, \u201CThe Lord has torn the kingdom of Israel
        from you today and has given it to your neighbor, who is better than you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Also the Splendor and Glory and Eminence of Israel will not lie or
        change His mind; for He is not a man that He should change His mind.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Saul said, \u201CI have sinned; but please honor me now before the
        elders of my people and before Israel, and go back with me, so that I may
        worship the Lord your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So Samuel went back following Saul, and Saul worshiped the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Samuel said, \u201CBring me Agag, the king of the Amalekites.\u201D
        And Agag came to him cheerfully. And Agag said, \u201CSurely the bitterness
        of death has come to an end.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Samuel said, \u201CAs your sword has made women childless, so shall
        your mother be childless among women.\u201D And Samuel cut Agag in pieces
        before the Lord in Gilgal.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Samuel went to Ramah, but Saul went up to his house in Gibeah
        of Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: Samuel did not see Saul again until the day of his death, for Samuel
        grieved over Saul. And the Lord regretted that He had made Saul king over
        Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Samuel Goes to Bethlehem'
      title: Samuel Goes to Bethlehem
      number: 1
      content: "  The Lord said to Samuel, \u201CHow long will you grieve for Saul,
        when I have rejected him as king over Israel? Fill your horn with oil and
        go; I will send you to Jesse the Bethlehemite, for I have chosen a king for
        Myself among his sons.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Samuel said, \u201CHow can I go? When Saul hears about it, he
        will kill me.\u201D And the Lord said, \u201CTake a heifer from the herd
        with you and say, \u2018I have come to sacrifice to the Lord.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You shall invite Jesse to the sacrifice, and I will show you what
        you shall do [after that]; and you shall anoint for Me the one whom I designate.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Samuel did what the Lord said, and came to Bethlehem. And the
        elders of the city came trembling to meet him and said, \u201CDo you come
        in peace?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he said, \u201CIn peace; I have come to sacrifice to the Lord.
        Consecrate yourselves and come with me to the sacrifice.\u201D He also consecrated
        Jesse and his sons and invited them to the sacrifice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So it happened, when they had come, he looked at Eliab [the eldest
        son] and thought, \u201CSurely the Lord\u2019s anointed is before Him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the Lord said to Samuel, \u201CDo not look at his appearance
        or at the height of his stature, because I have rejected him. For the Lord
        sees not as man sees; for man looks at the outward appearance, but the Lord
        looks at the heart.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Jesse called Abinadab and had him pass before Samuel. But Samuel
        said, \u201CThe Lord has not chosen this one either.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Next Jesse had Shammah pass by. And Samuel said, \u201CThe Lord has
        not chosen him either.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesse had seven of his sons pass before Samuel. But Samuel said to
        Jesse, \u201CThe Lord has not chosen [any of] these.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: David Anointed'
      title: David Anointed
      number: 11
      content: "Then Samuel said to Jesse, \u201CAre all your sons here?\u201D Jesse
        replied, \u201CThere is still one left, the youngest; he is tending the sheep.\u201D
        Samuel said to Jesse, \u201CSend word and bring him; because we will not
        sit down [to eat the sacrificial meal] until he comes here.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Jesse sent word and brought him in. Now he had a ruddy complexion,
        with beautiful eyes and a handsome appearance. The Lord said [to Samuel],
        \u201CArise, anoint him; for this is he.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Samuel took the horn of oil and anointed David in the presence
        of his brothers; and the Spirit of the Lord came mightily upon David from
        that day forward. And Samuel arose and went to Ramah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now the Spirit of the Lord departed from Saul, and an evil spirit
        from the Lord tormented and terrified him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Saul\u2019s servants said to him, \u201CBehold, an evil spirit from
        God is tormenting you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Let our lord now command your servants who are here before you to
        find a man who plays skillfully on the harp; and when the evil spirit from
        God is on you, he shall play the harp with his hand, and you will be well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Saul told his servants, \u201CFind me a man who plays well and
        bring him to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "One of the young men said, \u201CBehold, I have seen a son of Jesse
        the Bethlehemite who is a skillful musician, a brave and competent man, a
        warrior, discerning (prudent, eloquent) in speech, and a handsome man; and
        the Lord is with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So Saul sent messengers to Jesse and said, \u201CSend me David your
        son, who is with the flock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Jesse took a donkey [loaded with] bread and a jug of wine and a young
        goat, and sent them to Saul with David his son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then David came to Saul and attended him. Saul loved him greatly
        and [later] David became his armor bearer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Saul sent word to Jesse, saying, \u201CPlease let David be my attendant,
        for he has found favor in my sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So it came about that whenever the [evil] spirit from God was on Saul,
        David took a harp and played it with his hand; so Saul would be refreshed
        and be well, and the evil spirit would leave him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Goliath\u2019s Challenge"
      title: "Goliath\u2019s Challenge"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Philistines gathered their armies for battle and were assembled
        at Socoh, which belongs to Judah; and they camped between Socoh and Azekah,
        in Ephes-dammim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Saul and the men of Israel were gathered together and they camped
        in the Valley of Elah, and assembled in battle formation to meet the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Philistines were standing on the mountain on one side and Israel
        was standing on the mountain on the other side, with the valley between them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then a champion came out from the camp of the Philistines named Goliath
        of Gath, whose height was six cubits and a span. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He had a bronze helmet on his head, and wore a coat of scale-armor
        (overlapping metal plates) which weighed 5,000 shekels of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He had bronze shin protectors on his legs and a bronze javelin hung
        between his shoulders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The [wooden] shaft of his spear was like a weaver\u2019s beam; the
        blade-head of his spear weighed  six hundred shekels of iron. And a shield-bearer
        walked in front of him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Goliath stood and shouted to the battle lines of Israel, saying to
        them, \u201CWhy have you come out to draw up for battle? Am I not the Philistine
        and are you not servants of Saul? Choose a man for yourselves and have him
        come down to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "If he is able to fight with me and kill me, then we will become your
        servants; but if I prevail against him and kill him, then you shall become
        our servants and serve us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Again the Philistine said, \u201CI defy the battle lines of Israel
        this day; give me a man so that we may fight together.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When Saul and all Israel heard these words of the Philistine, they
        were dismayed and greatly afraid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now David was the son of the Ephrathite of Bethlehem in Judah, named
        Jesse, who had eight sons. Jesse was old in the days of Saul, advanced in
        years among men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'His three older sons had followed Saul into battle. The names of
        his three sons who went to battle were Eliab, the firstborn; next, Abinadab;
        and third, Shammah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'David was the youngest. Now the three oldest followed Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "but David went back and forth from Saul to tend his father\u2019s
        flock at Bethlehem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The Philistine [Goliath] came out morning and evening, and took his
        stand for forty days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jesse said to David his son, \u201CTake for your brothers an
        ephah of this roasted grain and these ten loaves of bread and run quickly
        to the camp to your brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Also take these ten cuts of cheese to the commander of the unit.
        See how your brothers are doing and bring back news of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: David Accepts the Challenge'
      title: David Accepts the Challenge
      number: 19
      content: "Now they are with Saul and all the men of Israel in the Valley of
        Elah, fighting with the Philistines.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So David got up early in the morning, left the flock with a keeper,
        picked up the provisions and went just as Jesse had directed him. And he
        came to the encampment as the army was going out in battle formation shouting
        the battle cry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Israel and the Philistines drew up in battle formation, army against
        army. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then David left his provisions in the care of the supply keeper,
        and ran to the ranks and came and greeted his brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'As he was talking with them, behold, the champion, the Philistine
        of Gath named Goliath, was coming up from the army of the Philistines, and
        he spoke these same words again; and David heard him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When the men of Israel all saw the man, they fled from him, and were
        very frightened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The men of Israel said, \u201CHave you seen this man who is coming
        up? Surely he is coming up to defy Israel. The king will reward the man who
        kills him with great riches, and will give him his daughter [in marriage]
        and make his father\u2019s house (family) free [from taxes and service] in
        Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then David spoke to the men who were standing by him, \u201CWhat
        will be done for the man who kills this Philistine and removes the disgrace
        [of his taunting] from Israel? For who is this uncircumcised Philistine that
        he has taunted and defied the armies of the living God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The men told him, \u201CThat is what will be done for the man who
        kills him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Now Eliab his oldest brother heard what he said to the men; and Eliab\u2019s
        anger burned against David and he said, \u201CWhy have you come down here?
        With whom did you leave those few sheep in the wilderness? I know your presumption
        (overconfidence) and the evil of your heart; for you have come down in order
        to see the battle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But David said, \u201CWhat have I done now? Was it not just a [harmless]
        question?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: David Kills Goliath'
      title: David Kills Goliath
      number: 30
      content: 'Then David turned away from Eliab to someone else and asked the same
        question; and the people gave him the same answer as the first time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'When the words that David spoke were heard, the men reported them
        to Saul, and he sent for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "David said to Saul, \u201CLet no man\u2019s courage fail because
        of him (Goliath). Your servant will go out and fight with this Philistine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Saul said to David, \u201CYou are not able to go against this
        Philistine to fight him. For you are [only] a young man and he has been a
        warrior since his youth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But David said to Saul, \u201CYour servant was tending his father\u2019s
        sheep. When a lion or a bear came and took a lamb out of the flock, "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'I went out after it and attacked it and rescued the lamb from its
        mouth; and when it rose up against me, I seized it by its whiskers and struck
        and killed it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Your servant has killed both the lion and the bear; and this uncircumcised
        Philistine will be like one of them, since he has taunted and defied the
        armies of the living God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "David said, \u201CThe Lord who rescued me from the paw of the lion
        and from the paw of the bear, He will rescue me from the hand of this Philistine.\u201D
        And Saul said to David, \u201CGo, and may the Lord be with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then Saul dressed David in his garments and put a bronze helmet on
        his head, and put a coat of mail (armor) on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Then David fastened his sword over his armor and tried to walk, [but
        he could not,] because he was not used to them. And David said to Saul, \u201CI
        cannot go with these, because I am not used to them.\u201D So David took
        them off. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then he took his [shepherd\u2019s] staff in his hand and chose for
        himself five smooth stones out of the stream bed, and put them in his shepherd\u2019s
        bag which he had, that is, in his shepherd\u2019s pouch. With his sling in
        his hand, he approached the Philistine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The Philistine came and approached David, with his shield-bearer
        in front of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'When the Philistine looked around and saw David, he derided and disparaged
        him because he was [just] a young man, with a ruddy complexion, and a handsome
        appearance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "The Philistine said to David, \u201CAm I a dog, that you come to
        me with [shepherd\u2019s] staffs?\u201D And the Philistine cursed David by
        his gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "The Philistine also said to David, \u201CCome to me, and I will give
        your flesh to the birds of the sky and the beasts of the field.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Then David said to the Philistine, \u201CYou come to me with a sword,
        a spear, and a javelin, but I come to you in the name of the Lord of hosts,
        the God of the armies of Israel, whom you have taunted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'This day the Lord will hand you over to me, and I will strike you
        down and cut off your head. And I will give the corpses of the army of the
        Philistines this day to the birds of the sky and the wild beasts of the earth,
        so that all the earth may know that there is a God in Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "and that this entire assembly may know that the Lord does not save
        with the sword or with the spear; for the battle is the Lord\u2019s and He
        will hand you over to us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'When the Philistine rose and came forward to meet David, David ran
        quickly toward the battle line to meet the Philistine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'David put his hand into his bag and took out a stone and slung it,
        and it struck the Philistine on his forehead. The stone penetrated his forehead,
        and he fell face down on the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "So David triumphed over the Philistine with a sling and a stone,
        and he struck down the Philistine and killed him; but there was no sword
        in David\u2019s hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'So he ran and stood over the Philistine, grasped his sword and drew
        it out of its sheath and killed him, and cut off his head with it. When the
        Philistines saw that their [mighty] champion was dead, they fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'The men of Israel and Judah stood with a shout and pursued the Philistines
        as far as the entrance to the valley and the gates of Ekron. And the [fatally]
        wounded Philistines fell along the way to Shaaraim, even as far as Gath and
        Ekron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'The sons of Israel returned from their pursuit of the Philistines
        and plundered their camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Then David took the head of the Philistine and brought it to Jerusalem,
        but he put his weapons in his tent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: "When Saul saw David going out against the Philistine, he said to
        Abner the captain of the army, \u201CAbner, whose son is this young man?\u201D
        And Abner answered, \u201CBy your life, O king, I do not know.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "The king said, \u201CAsk whose son the young man is.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'When David returned from killing [Goliath] the Philistine, Abner
        took him and brought him before Saul with the head of the Philistine in his
        hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "Saul asked him, \u201CWhose son are you, young man?\u201D And David
        answered, \u201CI am the son of your servant Jesse of Bethlehem.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jonathan and David'
      title: Jonathan and David
      number: 1
      content: '  When David had finished speaking to Saul, the soul of Jonathan
        was bonded to the soul of David, and Jonathan loved him as himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Saul took David that day and did not let him return to his father\u2019s
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Jonathan made a covenant with David because he loved him as
        himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Jonathan stripped himself of the outer robe that he was wearing and
        gave it to David, with his armor, including his sword, his bow, and his belt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David went out wherever Saul sent him, and he acted wisely and
        prospered; and Saul appointed him over the men of war. And it pleased all
        the people and also Saul\u2019s servants.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'As they were coming [home], when David returned from killing the
        Philistine, the women came out of all the cities of Israel, singing and dancing,
        to meet King Saul with tambourines, [songs of] joy, and musical instruments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The women sang as they played and danced, saying,\u201CSaul has slain
        his thousands,And David his ten thousands.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Saul became very angry, for this saying displeased him; and
        he said, \u201CThey have ascribed to David ten thousands, but to me they
        have ascribed [only] thousands. Now what more can he have but the kingdom?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Saul Turns against David'
      title: Saul Turns against David
      number: 9
      content: 'Saul looked at David with suspicion [and jealously] from that day
        forward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now it came about on the next day that an evil spirit from God came
        forcefully on Saul, and he raved [madly] inside his house, while David was
        playing the harp with his hand, as usual; and there was a spear in Saul\u2019s
        hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Saul hurled the spear, for he thought, \u201CI will pin David to
        the wall.\u201D But David evaded him twice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now Saul was afraid of David, because the Lord was with him, but
        had departed from Saul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Saul had David removed from his presence and appointed him as
        his commander of a thousand; and he publicly associated with the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'David acted wisely and prospered in all his ways, and the Lord was
        with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When Saul saw that he was prospering greatly, he was afraid of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But all Israel and Judah loved David, because he publicly associated
        with them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul said to David, \u201CBehold I will give you my older daughter
        Merab as a wife; only be brave for me and fight the Lord\u2019s battles.\u201D
        For Saul thought, \u201CMy hand shall not be against him, but let the hand
        of the Philistines be against him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "David said to Saul, \u201CWho am I, and what is my life or my father\u2019s
        family in Israel, that I should be the king\u2019s son-in-law?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "19: David Marries Saul\u2019s Daughter"
      title: "David Marries Saul\u2019s Daughter"
      number: 19
      content: "But at the time when Merab, Saul\u2019s daughter, should have been
        given to David, she was [instead] given to Adriel the Meholathite as a wife.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now Michal, Saul\u2019s daughter, loved David; and when they told
        Saul, it pleased him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Saul said, \u201CI will give her to him so that she may become a
        snare (bad influence, source of trouble) to him, and that the hand of the
        Philistines may be against him.\u201D So Saul said to David for a second
        time, \u201CYou shall be my son-in-law today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Saul commanded his servants, \u201CSpeak to David secretly,
        saying, \u2018Listen, the king delights in you, and all his servants love
        you; now then, become the king\u2019s son-in-law.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So Saul\u2019s servants spoke these words to David. But David said,
        \u201CIs it a trivial thing in your sight to become a king\u2019s son-in-law,
        seeing that I am a poor man and insignificant?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The servants of Saul told him what David said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CThis is what you shall say to David: \u2018The
        king wants no dowry except a hundred foreskins of the Philistines, to take
        vengeance on the king\u2019s enemies.\u2019\u2009\u201D Now Saul\u2019s intention
        was to cause David\u2019s death at the hand of the Philistines. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When his servants told David these words, it pleased him to become
        the king\u2019s son-in-law. Before the time [for the marriage] arrived, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "David arose and went, he and his men, and killed two hundred Philistine
        men, and David brought their foreskins [as proof of death] and presented
        every one of them to the king, so that he might become the king\u2019s son-in-law.
        So Saul gave him Michal, his [younger] daughter, as a wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When Saul saw and knew that the Lord was with David, and that Michal,
        his daughter, loved him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Saul was even more afraid of David; and Saul became David\u2019s
        constant enemy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then the Philistine commanders (princes) came out to battle, and
        it happened as often as they did, that David acted more wisely and had more
        success than all Saul\u2019s servants. So his name was highly esteemed."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Protected from Saul'
      title: David Protected from Saul
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Saul told his son Jonathan and all his servants to kill David,
        but Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, greatly delighted in David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So he told David, \u201CSaul my father is seeking to kill you. Now
        then, please be on guard in the morning, and stay in a secret place and hide
        yourself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "As for me, I will go out and stand beside my father in the field
        where you are, and I will speak with my father about you, and if I learn
        anything, then I will tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jonathan spoke well of David to Saul his father and said to
        him, \u201CMay the king not sin against his servant David, since he has not
        sinned against you, and since his deeds have been very beneficial to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For he took his life in his hand and killed the Philistine, and the
        Lord brought about a great victory for all Israel; you saw it and rejoiced.
        Why then would you sin against innocent blood by killing David without a
        cause?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Saul listened to Jonathan and swore [an oath], \u201CAs the Lord
        lives, he shall not be put to death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Jonathan called David and told him all these things. And Jonathan
        brought David to Saul, and he was in his presence [serving him] as previously.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then there was war again, and David went out and fought with the
        Philistines and defeated them with a great slaughter, and they fled before
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then an evil spirit from the Lord came on Saul as he was sitting
        in his house with his spear in his hand, and David was playing the harp with
        his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Saul tried to pin David to the wall with the spear, but he escaped
        from Saul\u2019s presence, so that Saul only stuck the spear into the wall.
        Then David fled and escaped that night.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Saul sent messengers to David\u2019s house to watch for him,
        so that he might kill him in the morning. But Michal, David\u2019s wife,
        told him, \u201CIf you do not save your life tonight, tomorrow you will be
        killed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Michal let David down through the window, and he fled and escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Michal took the household idol and laid it on the bed, put a
        pillow of goats\u2019 hair at its head, and covered it with clothes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And when Saul sent messengers to take David, she said, \u201CHe is
        sick.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Saul sent the messengers [again] to see David, saying, \u201CBring
        him up to me on his bed [if necessary], so that I may kill him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the messengers came in, there was the household idol on the
        bed with a quilt of goats\u2019 hair at its head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Saul said to Michal, \u201CWhy have you deceived me like this and
        let my enemy go, so that he has escaped?\u201D Michal answered Saul, \u201CHe
        said to me, \u2018Let me go! Why should I kill you?\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So David fled and escaped and came to Samuel at Ramah, and told him
        everything that Saul had done to him. And he and Samuel went and stayed in
        Naioth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Saul was told, \u201CDavid is at Naioth in Ramah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Saul sent messengers to take David; but when they saw the group
        of prophets prophesying, and Samuel standing and presiding over them, the
        Spirit of God came on the messengers of Saul; and they also prophesied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Saul was informed, he sent other messengers, and they also prophesied.
        So Saul sent messengers again, the third time, and they prophesied as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Saul went to Ramah himself and came to the great well that is
        in Secu; and he asked, \u201CWhere are Samuel and David?\u201D And he was
        told, \u201CThey are at Naioth [with the prophets] in Ramah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So he went on to Naioth in Ramah; and the Spirit of God came upon
        him too, and he went along continually prophesying until he came to Naioth
        in Ramah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He also took off his [royal] robes [and armor] and prophesied before
        Samuel and lay down naked all that day and night. So they say, \u201CIs Saul
        also among the prophets?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David and Jonathan\u2019s Covenant"
      title: "David and Jonathan\u2019s Covenant"
      number: 1
      content: "  David fled from Naioth in Ramah and he came and said to Jonathan,
        \u201CWhat have I done? What is my guilt? What is my sin before (against)
        your father, that he is seeking my life?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Jonathan said to him, \u201CFar from it! You shall not die. My father
        does nothing important or insignificant without telling me. So why would
        he hide this thing from me? It is not so!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But David vowed again, saying \u201CYour father certainly knows that
        I have found favor in your sight, and he has said, \u2018Do not let Jonathan
        know this, or he will be worried.\u2019 But truly as the Lord lives and as
        your soul lives, there is hardly a step between me and death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jonathan said to David, \u201CWhatever you say, I will do for
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "David said to Jonathan, \u201CBehold, tomorrow is the New Moon [observance],
        and I should sit at the table to eat [the sacrificial meal] with the king;
        but let me go, so that I may hide myself in the field until the third evening. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "If your father misses me at all, then say, \u2018David earnestly
        asked permission from me to go to Bethlehem, his city, because it is the
        yearly sacrifice there for the entire family.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If he says, \u2018All right,\u2019 your servant will be safe; but
        if he is very angry, then be certain that he has decided on evil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Therefore show kindness to your servant, because you have brought
        your servant into a covenant of the Lord with you. But if there is iniquity
        (guilt) in me, kill me yourself; for why should you bring me to your father
        [to be killed]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jonathan said, \u201CFar be it from [happening to] you! In fact,
        if I indeed learn that my father has decided to harm you, would I not tell
        you about it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then David said to Jonathan, \u201CWho will tell me if your father
        answers you harshly?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Jonathan said to David, \u201CCome, let us go out into the field
        [to talk].\u201D So they went out to the field.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jonathan said to David, \u201CThe Lord, the God of Israel, is
        my witness! When I have sounded out my father about this time tomorrow, or
        the third day, behold, if he has a good feeling toward you, shall I not then
        send word to you and make it known to you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But if it pleases my father to do you harm, may the Lord do so to
        Jonathan, and more if I do not let you know about it and send you away, so
        that you may go in safety. And may the Lord be with you as He has been with
        my father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If I am still alive, will you not show me the lovingkindness and
        faithfulness of the Lord, so that I will not die? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "You shall never cut off your lovingkindness and faithfulness from
        my house, not even when the Lord cuts off every one of the enemies of David
        from the face of the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Jonathan made a covenant with the house of David. [He added,]
        \u201CMay the Lord require it at the hands of David\u2019s enemies. [that
        is, hold them accountable for any harm they inflict on David].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Jonathan made David vow again because of his love for him, for Jonathan
        loved him as himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jonathan said to David, \u201CTomorrow is the New Moon [festival],
        and you will be missed because your seat will be empty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When you have stayed for three days, you shall go down quickly and
        come to the place where you hid yourself on that eventful day [when my father
        tried to kill you], and shall stay by the stone Ezel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I will shoot three arrows to the side of it, as though I shot at
        a target. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And I will send a boy, saying, \u2018Go, find the arrows.\u2019 If
        I specifically say to the boy, \u2018Look, the arrows are on this side of
        you, get them,\u2019 then come [back to my father\u2019s table]; for it is
        safe for you and there is no danger, as the Lord lives. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But if I say to the boy, \u2018Look, the arrows are beyond you,\u2019
        then go, for the Lord has sent you away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "As for the agreement of which you and I have spoken, behold, the
        Lord is between you and me forever [making sure that we each keep our word].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So David hid in the field; and when the New Moon [festival] came,
        the king sat down to eat food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The king sat on his seat as on previous occasions, on his seat by
        the wall; then Jonathan stood up, and Abner [his commander] sat down by Saul\u2019s
        side, but David\u2019s place was empty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Yet Saul did not say anything that day, for he thought, \u201CIt
        is an incident [of some kind] and he is not [ceremonially] clean\u2014surely
        he is unclean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But on the next day, the second day of the new moon, David\u2019s
        place was empty [again]; and Saul said to Jonathan his son, \u201CWhy has
        the son of Jesse not come to the meal, either yesterday or today?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Jonathan answered Saul, \u201CDavid earnestly asked me for permission
        to go to Bethlehem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Saul Is Angry with Jonathan'
      title: Saul Is Angry with Jonathan
      number: 29
      content: "He said, \u2018Please let me go because our family is holding a sacrifice
        in the city, and my brother has commanded me to attend. Now, if I have found
        favor in your eyes, please let me slip away so that I may see my brothers.\u2019
        That is why he has not come to the king\u2019s table.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Saul\u2019s anger burned against Jonathan and he said to him,
        \u201CYou son of a wayward, rebellious woman! Do I not know that you have
        chosen the son of Jesse [over me] to your own shame, and to the shame of
        your mother\u2019s nakedness? "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "For as long as the son of Jesse lives on the earth, neither you [as
        heir to the throne] nor your kingdom will be established. So now, send [someone]
        and bring him to me, for he must die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Jonathan answered Saul his father, \u201CWhy must he be put to death?
        What has he done?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then Saul hurled his spear at him to strike him down, so Jonathan
        knew [without any doubt] that his father had decided to put David to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Jonathan stood up from the table in the heat of anger, and ate
        no food on that second day of the new moon (month), for he grieved and worried
        about David because his father had dishonored him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'In the morning Jonathan went out to the field for the meeting with
        David, and a young boy was with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And he said to his boy, \u201CRun, please find the arrows which I
        am about to shoot.\u201D As the boy ran, he shot an arrow past him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "When the boy came to the place where Jonathan had shot the arrow,
        Jonathan called to him, \u201CIs the arrow not beyond you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Jonathan called out after the boy, \u201CHurry, be quick, do
        not stay!\u201D So Jonathan\u2019s boy picked up the arrow and came back
        to his master. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'But the boy was not aware of anything; only Jonathan and David knew
        about the matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Jonathan gave his weapons to his boy and said to him, \u201CGo, take
        them to the city.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'As soon as the boy was gone, David got up from the south side [beside
        the mound of stones] and fell on his face to the ground [in submission and
        respect], and bowed three times. Then they kissed one another and wept together,
        but David wept more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Jonathan told David, \u201CGo in safety, inasmuch as we have sworn
        to each other in the name of the Lord, saying, \u2018The Lord shall be between
        me and you, and between my descendants and yours forever.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        Then he stood and left, while Jonathan went into the city."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Takes Consecrated Bread'
      title: David Takes Consecrated Bread
      number: 1
      content: "  Then David went to Nob to Ahimelech the priest; and Ahimelech came
        trembling [in fear] to meet David and said to him, \u201CWhy are you alone,
        and no one with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David said to Ahimelech the priest, \u201CThe king has commissioned
        me with a matter and has told me, \u2018Let no one know anything about the
        matter for which I am sending you and with which I have commissioned you.
        I have directed the young men to a certain place.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now what [food] do you have on hand? Give me five loaves of bread,
        or whatever can be found.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The priest answered David, \u201CThere is no ordinary (unconsecrated)
        bread on hand, but there is consecrated bread; [you may have it] if only
        the young men have kept themselves from women.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "David answered the priest, \u201CBe assured that women have been
        kept from us in these three days since I set out, and the bodies of the young
        men were consecrated (ceremonially clean), although it was an ordinary (unconsecrated)
        journey; so how much more will their vessels be holy today?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the priest gave him the consecrated bread; for there was no bread
        there except the bread of the Presence which was removed from before the
        Lord in order to put hot bread in its place when it was taken away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now one of Saul\u2019s servants was there that day, detained before
        the Lord; his name was Doeg the Edomite, the chief of Saul\u2019s shepherds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "David said to Ahimelech, \u201CDo you not have a sword or spear here
        on hand? For I brought neither my sword nor my [other] weapons with me, because
        the king\u2019s business was urgent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the priest said, \u201CThe sword of Goliath the Philistine,
        whom you killed in the Valley of Elah, is here wrapped in a cloth behind
        the ephod; if you would take it for yourself, do so. For there is no other
        here except for it.\u201D And David said, \u201CThere is none like that;
        give it to me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then David arose and fled from Saul that day, and went to Achish
        king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The servants of Achish said to him, \u201CIs this not David the king
        of the land? Did they not sing in praise of this one as they danced, saying,\u2018Saul
        has slain his thousands,And David his ten thousands\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'David took these words to heart and was greatly afraid of Achish
        king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So [fearing for his life] he changed his behavior in their sight,
        and acted insanely in their hands, and he scribbled on the doors of the gate,
        and drooled on his beard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Achish said to his servants, \u201CLook, you see that the man
        is insane. Why have you brought him to me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Do I lack madmen, that you bring this one to behave like a madman
        in my presence? Shall this one come into my house?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Priests Slain at Nob'
      title: The Priests Slain at Nob
      number: 1
      content: "  So David departed from there and escaped to the cave of Adullam;
        and when his brothers and all his father\u2019s house heard about it, they
        went down there to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Everyone who was suffering hardship, and everyone who was in debt,
        and everyone who was discontented gathered to him; and he became captain
        over them. There were about four hundred men with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And David went from there to Mizpah of Moab; and he said to the king
        of Moab, \u201CPlease let my father and my mother come [out of Judah] and
        stay with you until I know what God will do for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then he left them with the king of Moab; and they stayed with him
        all the time that David was in the stronghold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the prophet Gad said to David, \u201CDo not stay in the stronghold;
        leave, and go into the land of Judah.\u201D So David left and went into the
        forest of Hereth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But Saul heard that David and the men who were with him had been
        discovered. Now Saul was in Gibeah, sitting under the tamarisk tree on the
        high place with his spear in his hand, and all his servants were standing
        around him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Saul said to his servants who were standing around him, \u201CListen
        now, you Benjamites! Will the son of Jesse also give every one of you fields
        and vineyards? Will he make you all commanders of thousands and hundreds? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For all of you have conspired against me so that no one informs me
        when my son [Jonathan] makes a covenant with the son of Jesse. None of you
        cares about me or informs me that my son has stirred up my servant against
        me to lie in ambush, as he does this day?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Doeg the Edomite, who was standing with Saul\u2019s servants,
        replied, \u201CI saw the son of Jesse coming to Nob, to Ahimelech [the priest]
        the son of Ahitub. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Ahimelech inquired of the Lord for him, and gave him provisions and
        the sword of Goliath the Philistine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the king sent someone to call Ahimelech the priest, the son
        of Ahitub, and all his father\u2019s household, the priests who were at Nob;
        and all of them came to the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CListen now, son of Ahitub.\u201D He replied,
        \u201CHere I am [at your service], my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Saul said to him, \u201CWhy have you and the son of Jesse conspired
        against me, in that you have given him bread and a sword and have inquired
        of God for him, so he would rebel against me by lying in ambush, as he does
        this day?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Ahimelech answered the king, \u201CAnd who among all your servants
        is as faithful and trustworthy as David, who is the king\u2019s son-in-law,
        and who is captain over your guard [and your confidant], and is honored in
        your house? "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Did I just begin to inquire of God for him today? Far be it from
        me! Do not let the king impute any guilt to his servant or to any of the
        household of my father, for your servant knows nothing at all about this
        entire matter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Saul said, \u201CBe assured that you shall die, Ahimelech, you
        and all your father\u2019s household (extended family).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the king said to the guards who stood around him, \u201CTurn
        around and kill the priests of the Lord, because their loyalty also is with
        David, and because they knew that he was fleeing and did not inform me.\u201D
        But the servants of the king were not willing to put out their hands to attack
        the Lord\u2019s priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So the king said to Doeg, \u201CYou turn around and attack the priests.\u201D
        And Doeg the Edomite turned and attacked the priests, and that day he killed
        eighty-five men who wore the [priest\u2019s] linen ephod. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And he struck Nob the city of the priests with the edge of the sword,
        both men and women, children and infants; also he struck oxen and donkeys
        and sheep with the edge of the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But one of the sons of Ahimelech the son of Ahitub, named Abiathar,
        escaped and fled to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Abiathar told David that Saul had murdered the Lord\u2019s priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then David said to Abiathar, \u201CI knew that day, when Doeg the
        Edomite was there, that he would certainly tell Saul. I have brought about
        the death of everyone in your father\u2019s household (extended family). "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Stay with me; do not be afraid, for he who seeks my life seeks your
        life, but you are safe with me.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Rescues Keilah'
      title: David Rescues Keilah
      number: 1
      content: "  Then they told David, saying, \u201CBehold, the Philistines are
        fighting against Keilah and are plundering (robbing) the threshing floors
        [of the grain].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So David inquired of the Lord, saying, \u201CShall I go and attack
        these Philistines?\u201D And the Lord said to David, \u201CGo and attack
        the Philistines and save Keilah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But David\u2019s men said to him, \u201CListen, we are afraid here
        in Judah. How much more then if we go to Keilah against the battle lines
        of the Philistines?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then David inquired of the Lord again. And the Lord answered him,
        \u201CArise, go down to Keilah, for I will hand over the Philistines to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So David and his men went to Keilah and fought the Philistines; he
        drove away their cattle and struck them with a great slaughter. So David
        rescued the inhabitants of Keilah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When Abiathar the son of Ahimelech fled to David at Keilah, he came
        down with an ephod in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now when Saul was informed that David had come to Keilah, Saul said,
        \u201CGod has handed him over to me, for he shut himself in by entering a
        city that has double gates and bars.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So Saul summoned all the people (soldiers) for war, to go down to
        Keilah to besiege David and his men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But David knew that Saul was plotting evil against him; and he said
        to Abiathar the priest, \u201CBring the ephod here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then David said, \u201CO Lord, the God of Israel, Your servant has
        heard for certain that Saul intends to come to Keilah, to destroy the city
        on my account. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Will the men of Keilah hand me over to him? Will Saul come down just
        as Your servant has heard? O Lord, God of Israel, I pray, tell Your servant.\u201D
        And the Lord said, \u201CHe will come down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then David asked, \u201CWill the men of Keilah surrender me and my
        men to Saul?\u201D The Lord said, \u201CThey will surrender you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then David and his men, about six hundred, arose and left Keilah,
        and they went wherever they could go. When Saul was told that David had escaped
        from Keilah, he gave up the pursuit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Saul Pursues David'
      title: Saul Pursues David
      number: 14
      content: 'David stayed in the wilderness in strongholds, in the hill country
        of the Wilderness of Ziph. Saul searched for him every day, but God did not
        hand David over to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now David became aware that Saul had come out to seek his life. David
        was in the Wilderness of Ziph [in the woods] at Horesh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Jonathan, Saul\u2019s son, arose and went [into the woods] to
        David at Horesh, and encouraged him in God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He said to him, \u201CDo not be afraid; the hand of my father Saul
        will not find you. You will be king over Israel and I will be second in command
        to you; my father Saul knows this too.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So the two of them made a covenant before the Lord; and David stayed
        [in the woods] at Horesh and Jonathan went to his house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Ziphites came to Saul at Gibeah, saying, \u201CIs David
        not hiding with us in strongholds of Horesh, on the hill of Hachilah, which
        is south of Jeshimon? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now then, O king, come down [to Ziph] in accordance with all your
        heart\u2019s desire to do so [and capture him]; and our part shall be to
        hand him over to the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Saul said, \u201CMay you be blessed by the Lord, because you have
        had compassion on me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Go now, be very persistent and investigate, and see where his haunt
        is and who has seen him there; for I am told he is very cunning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So look, and take note of all the places where he hides and come
        back to me with the established facts, then I will go with you. If he is
        [anywhere] in the land, I will search him out among all the thousands of
        Judah.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So they arose and went to Ziph ahead of Saul. Now David and his men
        were in the Wilderness of Maon, in the Arabah south of Jeshimon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Saul and his men went to search for him. When David was told
        about it, he went down to the rock and stayed [there] in the Wilderness of
        Maon. When Saul heard it, he pursued David in the Wilderness of Maon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Saul went on one side of the mountain, and David and his men on the
        other side of the mountain. And David was hurrying to get away from Saul,
        for Saul and his men were surrounding David and his men to capture them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But a messenger came to Saul, saying, \u201CHurry and come, because
        the Philistines have attacked the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Saul returned from pursuing David and went to meet the Philistines;
        therefore they called that place the Rock of Escape. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: David went up from there and stayed in the strongholds of Engedi.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David Spares Saul\u2019s Life"
      title: "David Spares Saul\u2019s Life"
      number: 1
      content: "  When Saul returned from following the Philistines, he was told,
        \u201CBehold, David is in the Wilderness of Engedi.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Saul took three thousand chosen men out of all Israel and went
        to search for David and his men in front of the Rocks of the Wild Goats. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "On the way he came to the sheepfolds where there was a cave; and
        Saul went in to relieve himself. Now David and his men were sitting in the
        cave\u2019s innermost recesses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "David\u2019s men said to him, \u201CBehold, this is the day of which
        the Lord said to you, \u2018Behold, I will hand over your enemy to you, and
        you shall do to him as seems good to you.\u2019\u2009\u201D Then David arose
        [in the darkness] and stealthily cut off the hem (edge) of Saul\u2019s robe. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Afterward, David\u2019s conscience bothered him because he had cut
        off the hem of Saul\u2019s robe.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said to his men, \u201CThe Lord forbid that I should do this thing
        to my master, the Lord\u2019s anointed, to put out my hand against him, since
        he is the anointed of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So David strongly rebuked his men with these words and did not let
        them rise up against Saul. Saul got up, left the cave and went on his way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then David also got up afterward and went out of the cave and called
        after Saul, saying, \u201CMy lord the king!\u201D And when Saul looked behind
        him, David bowed with his face to the ground and lay himself face down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "David said to Saul, \u201CWhy do you listen to the words of men who
        say, \u2018David seeks to harm you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Behold, your eyes have seen today how the Lord had given you into
        my hand in the cave. Some told me to kill you, but I spared you; I said,
        \u2018I will not reach out my hand against my lord, for he is the Lord\u2019s
        anointed.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Look, my father! Indeed, see the hem of your robe in my hand! Since
        I cut off the hem of your robe and did not kill you, know and understand
        [without question] that there is no evil or treason in my hands. I have not
        sinned against you, though you are lying in wait to take my life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'May the Lord judge between me and you; and may the Lord avenge me
        on you; but my hand shall not be against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As the proverb of the ancients says, \u2018Out of the wicked comes
        wickedness\u2019; but my hand shall not be against you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'After whom has the king of Israel come out? Whom do you pursue [with
        three thousand men]? A dead dog, a single flea? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "May the Lord be the judge and render judgment between me and you;
        and may He see and plead my cause and vindicate me by saving me from your
        hand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When David had finished saying these words to Saul, Saul said, \u201CIs
        this your voice, my son David?\u201D Then Saul raised his voice and wept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He said to David, \u201CYou are more righteous and upright [in God\u2019s
        eyes] than I; for you have done good to me, but I have done evil to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You have declared today the good that you have done to me, for when
        the Lord put me into your hand, you did not kill me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For if a man finds his enemy, will he let him go away unharmed? So
        may the Lord reward you with good in return for what you have done for me
        this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now, behold, I know that you will certainly be king and that the
        kingdom of Israel will be established in your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So now swear to me by the Lord that you will not cut off my descendants
        after me and that you will not destroy my name from my father\u2019s household
        (extended family).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: David gave Saul his oath; and Saul went home, but David and his men
        went up to the mountain stronghold.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Samuel\u2019s DeathNabal and Abigail"
      title: "Samuel\u2019s DeathNabal and Abigail"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Samuel died; and all Israel assembled and mourned for him,
        and they buried him at his house in Ramah. Then David left and went down
        to the Wilderness of Paran.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now there was a man in Maon whose business and possessions were in
        Carmel; and the man was very rich. He had three thousand sheep and a thousand
        goats, and he was shearing his sheep in Carmel '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "(now the man\u2019s name was Nabal and his wife\u2019s name was Abigail.
        She was intelligent and beautiful in appearance, but the man was harsh and
        evil in his dealings; he was a Calebite). "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David heard in the wilderness that Nabal was shearing his sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So David sent ten young men; and David said to the young men, \u201CGo
        up to Carmel and go to Nabal, and greet him in my name; "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and this is what you shall say, \u2018Have a long life! Peace be
        to you, and peace to your house, and peace to all that you have. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now I have heard that you have shearers. Now your shepherds have
        been with us and we have not harmed them, nor were they missing anything
        all the time they were in Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Ask your young men and they will tell you. Therefore let my young
        men find favor in your sight [and be well-treated], for we have come on a
        good (festive) day. Please, give whatever you find at hand to your servants
        and to your son David.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When David\u2019s young men came, they spoke to Nabal according to
        all these words in the name of David; then they waited. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Nabal answered David\u2019s servants and said, \u201CWho is David?
        And who is the son of Jesse? There are many servants today, each of whom
        is breaking away from his master. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So should I take my bread and my water and my meat that I have slaughtered
        for my shearers, and give it to men when I do not know where they are from?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So David\u2019s young men made their way back and returned; and they
        came and told him everything that was said [to them by Nabal]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "David said to his men, \u201CEach man put on your sword.\u201D So
        each man put on his sword. David also put on his sword, and about four hundred
        men went up behind David while two hundred stayed back with the provisions
        and supplies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But one of Nabal\u2019s young men told Abigail, Nabal\u2019s wife,
        \u201CListen, David sent messengers out of the wilderness to bless (greet)
        our master, and he shouted at them [in contempt]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But David\u2019s men were very good to us, and we were not harmed
        or treated badly, nor did we miss anything as long as we were with them,
        when we were in the fields. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They were a wall [of protection] to us both night and day, all the
        time that we were with them tending the sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Abigail Intercedes'
      title: Abigail Intercedes
      number: 17
      content: "Now then, know this and consider what you should do, for evil is
        [already] planned against our master and against all his household; but he
        is such a worthless and wicked man that one cannot speak [reasonably] to
        him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Abigail hurried and took two hundred loaves of bread, two jugs
        of wine, five sheep already prepared [for roasting], five measures of roasted
        grain, a hundred clusters of raisins, and two hundred cakes of figs, and
        loaded them on donkeys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "She said to her young men (servants), \u201CGo on ahead of me; behold,
        I am coming after you.\u201D But she did not tell her husband Nabal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'It happened that as she was riding on her donkey and coming down
        by [way of] the hidden part of the mountain, that suddenly David and his
        men were coming down toward her, and she met them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now David had said, \u201CSurely in vain I have protected and guarded
        all that this man has in the wilderness, so that nothing was missing of all
        that belonged to him; and he has repaid me evil for good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "May God do so to the enemies of David, and more also, if by morning
        I leave [alive] even one male of any who belong to him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When Abigail saw David, she hurried and dismounted from the donkey,
        and kneeled face downward before David and bowed down to the ground [in respect]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Kneeling at his feet she said, \u201CMy lord, let the blame and guilt
        be on me alone. And please let your maidservant speak to you, and listen
        to the words of your maidservant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Please do not let my lord pay attention to this worthless man, Nabal,
        for as his name is, so is he. Nabal (fool) is his name and foolishness (stupidity)
        is with him; but I your maidservant did not see my lord\u2019s young men
        whom you sent.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So now, my lord, as the Lord lives, and as your soul lives, since
        the Lord has prevented you from shedding blood, and from avenging yourself
        by your own hand, now then let your enemies and those who seek to do evil
        to my lord, be as [self-destructive as] Nabal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now this gift, which your maidservant has brought my lord, let it
        be given to the young men who accompany and follow my lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Please forgive the transgression of your maidservant; for the Lord
        will certainly make my lord a secure and enduring house, because my lord
        is fighting the battles of the Lord, and evil will not be found in you all
        your days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Should anyone rise up to pursue you and to seek your life, then the
        life of my lord will be bound in the [precious] bundle of the living with
        the Lord your God; but the lives of your enemies\u2014those He will hurl
        out as from the center of a sling. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And it will happen when the Lord does for my lord according to all
        the good that He has spoken (promised) concerning you, and appoints you ruler
        over Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "that this [incident] will not cause grief or [bring] a troubled conscience
        to my lord, both by having shed blood without cause and by my lord having
        avenged himself. When the Lord deals well with my lord, then remember [with
        favor] your maidservant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "David said to Abigail, \u201CBlessed be the Lord, the God of Israel,
        who sent you to meet me this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And blessed be your discretion and discernment, and blessed be you,
        who has kept me from bloodshed this day and from avenging myself by my own
        hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Nevertheless, as the Lord the God of Israel lives, who has prevented
        me from harming you, if you had not come quickly to meet me, most certainly
        by the morning light there would not have been left to Nabal so much as one
        male.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "So David accepted what she had brought to him and said to her, \u201CGo
        up to your house in peace. See, I have listened to you and have granted your
        request.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Abigail came to Nabal, and he was holding a feast in his house
        [for the shearers], like the feast of a king. And Nabal\u2019s mood was joyous
        because he was very drunk; so she told him nothing at all until the morning
        light. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'But in the morning, when Nabal was sober, and his wife told him these
        things, his heart died within him and he became [paralyzed and helpless]
        like a stone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: David Marries Abigail'
      title: David Marries Abigail
      number: 38
      content: 'About ten days later, the Lord struck Nabal and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "When David heard that Nabal was dead, he said, \u201CBlessed be the
        Lord, who has pleaded the cause of my reproach [suffered] at the hand of
        Nabal and has kept His servant from [retaliating with] evil. For the Lord
        has returned the wickedness of Nabal on his own head.\u201D Then David sent
        word to Abigail, proposing to take her as his wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "When the servants of David came to Abigail at Carmel, they said to
        her, \u201CDavid sent us to you to take you [to him] to be his wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And she stood and bowed with her face to the ground and said, \u201CBehold,
        your maidservant is [ready to be] a maid to wash the feet of the servants
        of my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Then Abigail quickly got up, and rode on a donkey, with five of her
        maidens who attended her; and she followed the messengers of David and became
        his wife.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'David had also taken Ahinoam of Jezreel, and they both became his
        wives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "But Saul had given Michal his [younger] daughter, David\u2019s wife,
        to Palti the son of Laish, who was from Gallim."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Again Spares Saul'
      title: David Again Spares Saul
      number: 1
      content: "  The Ziphites came to Saul at Gibeah, saying, \u201CIs David not
        hiding on the hill of Hachilah, east of Jeshimon?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Saul arose and went down to the Wilderness of Ziph, taking with
        him three thousand chosen men of Israel, to search for David [there] in the
        wilderness of Ziph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Saul camped on the hill of Hachilah, which is beside the road east
        of Jeshimon, but David stayed in the wilderness. When he saw that Saul came
        into the wilderness after him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'David sent out spies, and he learned that Saul was definitely coming. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So David arose and went to the place where Saul had camped, and saw
        the spot where Saul lay, as well as Abner the son of Ner, the commander of
        his army; and Saul was lying inside the circle of the camp, with the army
        camped around him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then David said to Ahimelech the Hittite and to Abishai the son of
        Zeruiah, brother of Joab, \u201CWho will go down with me to Saul in the camp?\u201D
        And Abishai said, \u201CI will go down with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So David and Abishai went to the army during the night, and there
        was Saul lying asleep inside the circle of the camp with his spear stuck
        in the ground by his head; and Abner and the people were lying around him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Abishai said to David, \u201CGod has given your enemy into your
        hand this day; now then, please let me strike him with the spear driving
        it to the ground with one stroke, and I will not strike him the second time.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But David said to Abishai, \u201CDo not kill him, for who can put
        out his hand against the Lord\u2019s anointed [king] and be guiltless (innocent)?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "David also said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, most certainly the Lord
        will strike him [in His own time and way], or his day will come and he will
        die, or he will go down into battle and be carried off [dead]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The Lord forbid that I would put out my hand against the Lord\u2019s
        anointed; but now take the spear that is by his head and the jug of water,
        and let us go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So David took the spear and the jug of water from beside Saul\u2019s
        head, and they left, and no one saw or knew nor did anyone awaken, because
        they were all sound asleep, for a deep sleep from the Lord had fallen on
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then David crossed over to the other side and stood on the top of
        the mountain at a distance, with a large area between them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "David called to the army and to Abner the son of Ner, \u201CWill
        you not answer, Abner?\u201D Abner replied, \u201CWho are you who calls [and
        disturbs] the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "David said to Abner, \u201CAre you not a [brave] man? Who is like
        you in Israel? Why then have you not guarded your lord the king? For one
        of the people came [into your camp] to kill the king your lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "This thing that you have done is not good. As the Lord lives, you
        surely deserve to die, because you have not guarded your lord, the Lord\u2019s
        anointed. And now, see where the king\u2019s spear is, and the jug of water
        that was by his head.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Saul recognized David\u2019s voice and said, \u201CIs this your
        voice, my son David?\u201D And David said, \u201CIt is my voice, my lord
        the king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And David said, \u201CWhy is my lord pursuing his servant? For what
        have I done? Or what evil is in my hand? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now therefore, please let my lord the king hear the words of his
        servant. If the Lord has incited you against me, let Him accept an offering
        [from me]; but if it is men, may they be cursed before the Lord, because
        they have driven me out this day to keep me from sharing in the inheritance
        of the Lord, saying, \u2018Go, serve other gods.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now then, do not let my blood fall to the ground away from the presence
        of the Lord; for the king of Israel has come out to search for a single flea,
        just as when one hunts a [defenseless] partridge in the mountains.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Saul said, \u201CI have sinned. Return, my son David, for I
        will not harm you again because my life was precious in your sight this day.
        Hear me, I have played the fool and have done a very great wrong [to you].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "David answered, \u201CLook, here is the king\u2019s spear! Now let
        one of the young men come over and get it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The Lord will repay each man for his righteousness and his faithfulness;
        for the Lord handed you over to me today, but I refused to put out my hand
        against the Lord\u2019s anointed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Now behold, just as your life was precious in my sight this day,
        so let my life be precious in the sight of the Lord, and may He rescue me
        from all distress.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Saul said to David, \u201CMay you be blessed, my son David;
        you will both accomplish much and certainly prevail.\u201D So David went
        on his way, and Saul returned to his place."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David Flees to the Philistines'
      title: David Flees to the Philistines
      number: 1
      content: "  But David said in his heart, \u201CNow I will die one day by the
        hand of Saul. There is nothing better for me than to escape to the land of
        the Philistines. Then Saul will give up searching for me inside the borders
        of Israel, and I will escape from his hand [once and for all].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So David and the six hundred men who were with him arose and crossed
        over to Achish the son of Maoch, king of Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And David lived with Achish at Gath, he and his men, each man with
        his household, and David with his two wives, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and
        Abigail the Carmelitess, [who was] Nabal\u2019s widow. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When Saul was told that David had fled to Gath, he no longer searched
        for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then David said to Achish, \u201CIf I have found favor in your sight,
        let me be given a place [of my own] in one of the cities in the country,
        so that I may live there; for why should your servant live in the royal city
        with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Achish gave David [the town of] Ziklag that day. Therefore Ziklag
        has belonged to the kings of Judah to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The number of days that David lived in the country of the Philistines
        was a year and four months.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now David and his men went up and raided the Geshurites, the Girzites,
        and the Amalekites [the enemies of Israel that Joshua had failed to annihilate];
        for they had inhabited the land from ancient times, as one comes to Shur
        even as far as the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'David attacked the land and did not leave a man or a woman alive,
        but he took the sheep, the cattle, the donkeys, the camels, and the clothing,
        and returned to Achish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "When Achish asked, \u201CWhere did you raid today?\u201D David replied,
        \u201CAgainst the Negev (the South country) of Judah, and against the Negev
        of the Jerahmeelites, and against the Negev of the Kenites.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "David did not leave a man or a woman alive to bring news to Gath,
        saying [to himself], \u201COtherwise they will tell about us, saying, \u2018This
        is what David has done, and this has been his practice all the time that
        he has lived in the country of the Philistines.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Achish believed David, saying, \u201CHe has certainly become hated
        by his people in Israel; so he will always be my servant.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul and the Spirit Medium'
      title: Saul and the Spirit Medium
      number: 1
      content: "  In those days the Philistines gathered their forces for war to
        fight against Israel. Achish said to David, \u201CUnderstand for certain
        that you and your men will go out with me to battle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "David said to Achish, \u201CAll right, you shall know what your servant
        can do.\u201D So Achish said to David, \u201CTherefore I will make you my
        bodyguard for life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Samuel had died, and all Israel had mourned for him and buried
        him in Ramah, his own city. And Saul had removed the mediums and the spiritists
        (soothsayers) from the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Philistines assembled and came and camped at Shunem; and Saul
        gathered all the Israelites and they camped at Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When Saul saw the Philistine army, he was afraid and badly shaken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Saul inquired of the Lord, but the Lord did not answer him, either
        by dreams or by Urim [used like lots by the priest to determine the will
        of God] or by prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Saul said to his servants, \u201CFind for me a woman who is
        a medium [between the living and the dead], so that I may go to her and ask
        her advice.\u201D His servants said to him, \u201CThere is a woman who is
        a medium at En-dor.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Saul disguised himself by wearing different clothes, and he left
        with two men, and they came to the woman at night. He said to her, \u201CConjure
        up for me, please, and bring up [from the dead] for me [the spirit] whom
        I shall name to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But the woman said to him, \u201CSee here, you know what Saul has
        done, how he has cut off (eliminated) those who are mediums and spiritists
        from the land. So why are you laying a trap for my life, to cause my death?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Saul swore [an oath] to her by the Lord, saying, \u201CAs the
        Lord lives, no punishment shall come upon you for this.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the woman said, \u201CWhom shall I bring up for you?\u201D He
        said, \u201CBring up Samuel for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When the woman saw Samuel, she screamed with a loud voice; and she
        said to Saul, \u201CWhy have you deceived me? You are Saul!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The king said to her, \u201CDo not be afraid; but [tell me] what
        do you see?\u201D The woman said to Saul, \u201CI see a divine [superhuman]
        being coming up from the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He said to her, \u201CWhat is his appearance?\u201D And she said,
        \u201CAn old man is coming up, wrapped in a robe.\u201D Then Saul knew that
        it was Samuel, and he bowed with his face to the ground and paid respect
        [to him].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Samuel said to Saul, \u201CWhy have you disturbed me by bringing
        me up?\u201D Saul answered, \u201CI am greatly distressed; for the Philistines
        are making war against me, and God has left me and no longer answers me,
        either through prophets or by dreams; therefore I have called you to make
        known to me what I should do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Samuel said, \u201CWhy then do you ask me, since the Lord has left
        you and has become your enemy? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The Lord has done [to you] just as He said through me [when I was
        with you]; for the Lord has torn the kingdom out of your hand and given it
        to your neighbor, to David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Because you did not obey the voice of the Lord and did not execute
        His fierce wrath on Amalek, therefore the Lord has done this thing to you
        this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Moreover, the Lord will also put Israel along with you into the hands
        of the Philistines, and tomorrow you and your sons will be with me [among
        the dead]. Indeed, the Lord will put the army of Israel into the hands of
        the Philistines.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Saul immediately fell full length on the earth [floor of the
        medium\u2019s house], and was very afraid because of Samuel\u2019s words;
        and he was thoroughly exhausted because he had not eaten all day and all
        night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The woman came to Saul and saw that he was greatly troubled, and
        she said to him, \u201CLook, your maidservant has obeyed you, and I have
        taken my life in my hand and have listened to everything you said to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So now, please listen to the voice of your maidservant, and let me
        set a piece of bread before you, and eat, so that you may have strength when
        you go on your way.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But he refused and said, \u201CI will not eat.\u201D But his servants
        together with the woman urged him, and he [finally] listened to them. So
        he got up from the ground and sat on the bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The woman had a fattened calf in the house; she quickly killed it,
        and took flour, kneaded it and baked unleavened bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: She brought it before Saul and his servants, and they ate. Then they
        got up and went away that night.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Philistines Mistrust David'
      title: The Philistines Mistrust David
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Philistines gathered all their forces at Aphek, while Israel
        camped by the spring in Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'As the Philistine lords (governors) were proceeding on [marching]
        by hundreds and by thousands, and David and his men were proceeding on in
        the rear with Achish [the king of Gath], '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "the Philistine commanders [having noticed David] said, \u201CWhat
        are these Hebrews doing here?\u201D Achish said to the Philistine commanders,
        \u201CIs this not David, the servant of Saul king of Israel, who has been
        with me these days and years, and I have found no fault in him from the day
        he deserted to me to this day?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the Philistine commanders were angry with Achish and they said
        to him, \u201CMake this man return, so that he may go back to his place where
        you have assigned him, and do not let him go down to battle with us, or in
        the battle he may [turn and] become our adversary. For how could David reconcile
        himself to his lord [Saul]? Would it not be with the heads of these [Philistine]
        men? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Is this not David, of whom they used to sing in dances,\u2018Saul
        killed his thousands,And David his ten thousands\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Achish called David and said to him, \u201CAs the Lord lives,
        you have been upright (righteous), and your behavior in the army is pleasing
        in my sight. For from the day you came to me to this day I have found no
        evil in you. Nevertheless, the [Philistine] lords do not approve of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So return now and go in peace [to your place], so that you do not
        displease the Philistine lords.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "David said to Achish, \u201CBut what have I done? What have you found
        in your servant from the day when I [first] came before you to this day,
        that I may not go and fight against the enemies of my lord the king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Achish answered David, \u201CI know that you are blameless in my
        sight, like an angel of God; nevertheless the commanders of the Philistines
        have said, \u2018He must not go up with us to the battle.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So now, get up early in the morning with your master\u2019s servants
        who have come with you, and as soon as you are up in the morning and have
        light, leave.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: So David and his men got up early to leave in the morning, to return
        to the land of the Philistines. But the Philistines went up to Jezreel [to
        fight against Israel].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Victory over the Amalekites"
      title: "David\u2019s Victory over the Amalekites"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it happened when David and his men came [home] to Ziklag on
        the third day, [they found] that the Amalekites had made a raid on the Negev
        (the South country) and on Ziklag, and had overthrown Ziklag and burned it
        with fire; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and they had taken captive the women [and all] who were there, both
        small and great. They killed no one, but carried them off [to be used as
        slaves] and went on their way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When David and his men came to the town, it was burned, and their
        wives and their sons and their daughters had been taken captive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then David and the people who were with him raised their voices and
        wept until they were too exhausted to weep [any longer]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now David\u2019s two wives had been captured, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess
        and Abigail the widow of Nabal the Carmelite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Further, David was greatly distressed because the people spoke of
        stoning him, for all of them were embittered, each man for his sons and daughters.
        But David felt strengthened and encouraged in the Lord his God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "David said to Abiathar the priest, Ahimelech\u2019s son, \u201CPlease
        bring me the ephod.\u201D So Abiathar brought him the ephod. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "David inquired of the Lord, saying, \u201CShall I pursue this band
        [of raiders]? Will I overtake them?\u201D And He answered him, \u201CPursue,
        for you will certainly overtake them, and you will certainly rescue [the
        captives].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So David went, he and the six hundred men who were with him, and
        came to the brook Besor; there those [who could not continue] remained behind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But David pursued [the Amalekites], he and four hundred men, for
        two hundred who were too exhausted to cross the brook Besor stayed behind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They found an Egyptian [who had collapsed] in the field and brought
        him to David, and gave him bread and he ate, and they gave him water to drink, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and they gave him a piece of a fig cake and two clusters of raisins;
        and when he had eaten, his energy returned, for he had not eaten bread or
        had any water to drink for three days and three nights. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "David said to him, \u201CTo whom do you belong, and where are you
        from?\u201D He said, \u201CI am a young man from Egypt, a servant of an Amalekite;
        and my master abandoned me [as useless] when I fell sick three days ago. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "We made a raid on the Negev of the Cherethites, and on that which
        belongs to Judah, and on the Negev of Caleb, and we burned Ziklag with fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then David said to him, \u201CWill you take me down to this band
        [of raiders]?\u201D And he said, \u201CSwear to me by God that you will not
        kill me or turn me over to the hand of my master, and I will bring you down
        to this band.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When he brought David down, the Amalekites had disbanded and spread
        over all the land, eating and drinking and dancing because of all the great
        spoil they had taken from the land of the Philistines and from the land of
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then David [and his men] struck them down [in battle] from twilight
        until the evening of the next day; and not a man of them escaped, except
        four hundred young men who rode camels and fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So David recovered all that the Amalekites had taken, and rescued
        his two wives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Nothing of theirs was missing whether small or great, sons or daughters,
        spoil or anything that had been taken; David recovered it all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Spoils Are Divided'
      title: The Spoils Are Divided
      number: 20
      content: "So David captured all the flocks and herds [which the enemy had],
        and [the people] drove those animals before him and said, \u201CThis is David\u2019s
        spoil.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'David came to the two hundred men who were so exhausted that they
        could not follow him and had been left at the brook Besor [with the provisions].
        They went out to meet David and the people with him, and when he approached
        the people, he greeted them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then all the wicked and worthless men among those who went with David
        said, \u201CBecause they did not go with us, we will give them none of the
        spoil that we have recovered, except that each man may take his wife and
        children away and leave.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "David said, \u201CYou must not do so, my brothers, with what the
        Lord has given us. He has kept us safe and has handed over to us the band
        [of Amalekites] that came against us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And who will listen to you in regard to this matter? For as is the
        share of him who goes down into the battle, so shall his share be who stays
        by the provisions and supplies; they shall share alike.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So from that day forward he made it a statute and an ordinance for
        Israel to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When David came to Ziklag, he sent part of the spoil to the elders
        of Judah, his friends, saying, \u201CHere is a blessing (gift) for you from
        the spoil of the enemies of the Lord: "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For those in Bethel, Ramoth of the Negev, Jattir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Aroer, Siphmoth, Eshtemoa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Racal, the cities of the Jerahmeelites, the cities of the Kenites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Hormah, Bor-ashan, Athach, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Hebron, and for [those elders in] all the places where David himself
        and his men were accustomed to go.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Saul and His Sons Slain'
      title: Saul and His Sons Slain
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Philistines fought against Israel, and the men of Israel
        fled before them and fell slain on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Philistines overtook Saul and his sons; and they killed Jonathan
        and Abinadab and Malchi-shua, Saul\u2019s sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The battle went heavily against Saul, and the archers hit him; and
        he was severely wounded by the archers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Saul said to his armor bearer, \u201CDraw your sword and pierce me
        through with it, otherwise these uncircumcised [Philistines] will come and
        pierce me through and abuse and mock me.\u201D But his armor bearer would
        not, because he was terrified [of doing such a thing]. So Saul took his sword
        and fell on it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When his armor bearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell on his
        sword and died with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Saul, his three sons, his armor bearer, and all his men died together
        on that day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When the men of Israel who were on the other side of the valley [of
        Jezreel], and those who were beyond the Jordan, saw that the other men of
        Israel had fled and that Saul and his sons were dead, they abandoned the
        cities and fled; then the Philistines came and lived in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The next day, when the Philistines came to plunder the dead, they
        found Saul and his three sons fallen on Mount Gilboa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So they cut off Saul\u2019s head and stripped off his weapons and
        armor and sent them throughout the land of the Philistines, to bring the
        good news to the house of their idols and to the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And they put Saul\u2019s weapons and armor in the temple of the Ashtaroth
        (female goddesses), and they fastened his body to the wall of Beth-shan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When the inhabitants of Jabesh-gilead heard what the Philistines
        had done to Saul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'all the brave men stood and walked all night, and they took the bodies
        of Saul and his sons from the wall of Beth-shan, and they came to Jabesh
        and cremated them there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: They took their bones and buried them under the tamarisk tree at Jabesh,
        and fasted [as a sign of mourning and respect] for seven days.
      comments: []
